1
00:00:06,501 --> 00:00:08,918
[soft music]

2
00:00:12,209 --> 00:00:14,793
[dramatic music]

3
00:00:22,834 --> 00:00:25,043
[bright whimsical music]

4
00:00:34,376 --> 00:00:37,126
[grand music]

5
00:00:46,709 --> 00:00:49,293
[light music]

6
00:00:55,709 --> 00:01:01,209
[soft music]
[lyrics indistinct]

7
00:01:11,668 --> 00:01:16,543
♪ She says she
doesn't need to go ♪

8
00:01:16,626 --> 00:01:21,209
♪ So I don't let her know ♪

9
00:01:21,293 --> 00:01:24,501
♪ And then she smiles ♪

10
00:01:24,584 --> 00:01:30,251
♪ In her fantasy ♪

11
00:01:30,334 --> 00:01:32,334
[music continues muffled]

12
00:01:36,918 --> 00:01:38,001
[cat meowing]

13
00:01:38,418 --> 00:01:40,376
[laughing]

14
00:01:45,918 --> 00:01:47,459
Great, you got it everywhere.

15
00:01:47,626 --> 00:01:49,584
[cat purring]

16
00:01:50,126 --> 00:01:51,543
Nicky, stop.

17
00:01:51,626 --> 00:01:54,834
[music continues]
[lyrics indistinct]

18
00:02:03,709 --> 00:02:04,709
[meows]

19
00:02:09,168 --> 00:02:10,459
[knocking on door]

20
00:02:13,584 --> 00:02:14,668
Noctis Police, ma'am.

21
00:02:14,751 --> 00:02:16,418
[woman] Oh, that was fast.

22
00:02:16,501 --> 00:02:17,668
Yeah. Come in.

23
00:02:18,709 --> 00:02:20,584
Hey you... you got a little...

24
00:02:20,668 --> 00:02:21,668
Hmm?

25
00:02:21,876 --> 00:02:23,043
Mm-mm.

26
00:02:23,126 --> 00:02:25,126
No, it's... let me just.

27
00:02:26,251 --> 00:02:28,334
[gasping]

28
00:02:28,418 --> 00:02:29,793
[bones cracking] [gagging]

29
00:02:30,626 --> 00:02:34,126
[music continues]
[lyrics indistinct]

30
00:02:38,209 --> 00:02:40,501
[water running]

31
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:49,793
[gun firing]

32
00:02:56,793 --> 00:02:57,876
[door shuts]

33
00:02:58,126 --> 00:02:59,543
[gasping]

34
00:03:00,209 --> 00:03:03,126
[objects thudding]

35
00:03:08,876 --> 00:03:10,001
[breathes deeply]

36
00:03:11,084 --> 00:03:14,418
[music continues]
[lyrics indistinct]

37
00:03:17,543 --> 00:03:19,293
[beeping]

38
00:03:24,709 --> 00:03:25,459
[male voice] Hello?

39
00:03:25,543 --> 00:03:27,060
[woman on phone] <i>Your
appointment has arrived.</i>

40
00:03:27,084 --> 00:03:28,751
[male voice] Good,
show her up. Thank you.

41
00:03:28,834 --> 00:03:29,935
[woman] <i>While I have you, sir,</i>

42
00:03:29,959 --> 00:03:31,168
<i>you haven't indicated</i>

43
00:03:31,251 --> 00:03:32,852
<i>whether you'll be having
breakfast tomorrow?</i>

44
00:03:32,876 --> 00:03:34,144
[male voice] No,
I'm good. Thank you.

45
00:03:34,168 --> 00:03:35,876
[woman] <i>It's included
in your stay, sir.</i>

46
00:03:35,959 --> 00:03:37,959
Kind of you to offer,
but I'm a robot.

47
00:03:39,709 --> 00:03:40,709
[tsks]

48
00:03:43,959 --> 00:03:46,084
[traffic rumbling]

49
00:03:46,168 --> 00:03:47,168
She's coming.

50
00:03:48,626 --> 00:03:49,751
<i>Okay, I'm ready.</i>

51
00:03:49,834 --> 00:03:51,459
<i>Sorry you're taking
all the risks.</i>

52
00:03:51,543 --> 00:03:52,418
[LEM] It's fine.

53
00:03:52,501 --> 00:03:55,001
<i>Well, I'm just hoping she
doesn't give us any problems.</i>

54
00:03:56,626 --> 00:03:58,293
<i>Just be sure to
check her ID first.</i>

55
00:03:58,918 --> 00:04:00,876
- [LEM] You're breaking up.
<i>- Can you hear me?</i>

56
00:04:00,959 --> 00:04:03,119
- [LEM] Can you hear me?
<i>- Oh shit, it's getting worse.</i>

57
00:04:03,168 --> 00:04:04,959
<i>They're jamming our signal.</i>

58
00:04:05,043 --> 00:04:07,709
- Should we abort or what?
- [knocking on door]

59
00:04:14,209 --> 00:04:15,209
Hello.

60
00:04:16,209 --> 00:04:17,293
Were you jamming us?

61
00:04:17,376 --> 00:04:18,376
[Aline] Yeah.

62
00:04:18,834 --> 00:04:21,084
I didn't want the whole
world knowing our business.

63
00:04:21,168 --> 00:04:24,043
Trust me, we've taken
every security precaution.

64
00:04:24,126 --> 00:04:26,626
Your jamming actually
just impedes our work.

65
00:04:26,709 --> 00:04:27,709
Care for a drink?

66
00:04:28,084 --> 00:04:29,751
[fridge] <i>Sobriety
mode activated.</i>

67
00:04:29,918 --> 00:04:32,168
Yeah, I'm in AA at the moment.

68
00:04:32,251 --> 00:04:33,626
[LEM] Oh, sorry.

69
00:04:33,709 --> 00:04:35,168
You are aware of
the consequences

70
00:04:35,251 --> 00:04:36,501
of jail-breaking him.

71
00:04:36,584 --> 00:04:37,584
We got it.

72
00:04:37,668 --> 00:04:39,709
I'll no longer be
constrained by cyber laws.

73
00:04:39,793 --> 00:04:41,126
I'll be free to steal, kill,

74
00:04:41,209 --> 00:04:43,293
and even swear like a
sailor if I want to.

75
00:04:43,376 --> 00:04:46,043
I'll be an outlaw, subject
to disassembly if caught.

76
00:04:46,668 --> 00:04:48,293
So then will you be doing it?

77
00:04:48,376 --> 00:04:50,126
Where's the woman I
spoke with before?

78
00:04:50,501 --> 00:04:53,418
She'll be with us the moment
you switch off your jammer.

79
00:04:57,751 --> 00:04:58,959
[popping lips]

80
00:04:59,418 --> 00:05:02,376
<i>Hey, that's way better. Hello!</i>

81
00:05:02,834 --> 00:05:05,626
<i>Whoa, a Vigil-2? So retro.</i>

82
00:05:05,709 --> 00:05:07,126
<i>What OS are you packing?</i>

83
00:05:07,209 --> 00:05:08,043
ExOS 4.

84
00:05:08,126 --> 00:05:09,668
<i>Ah, very nice.</i>

85
00:05:09,751 --> 00:05:12,959
<i>Now LEM here is gonna scan
you, just a little formality.</i>

86
00:05:13,376 --> 00:05:14,376
If you don't mind.

87
00:05:16,459 --> 00:05:18,876
[Aline] <i>Find her. I've
got about five seconds.</i>

88
00:05:19,584 --> 00:05:20,824
[Carlos] <i>She's in the building.</i>

89
00:05:21,251 --> 00:05:23,876
<i>[tense music] [whirring]</i>

90
00:05:26,043 --> 00:05:28,251
<i>Just cross-referencing
my database.</i>

91
00:05:30,334 --> 00:05:32,251
[music continues]

92
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:36,209
[Aline] <i>Come on. Come on.</i>

93
00:05:37,126 --> 00:05:38,709
[Carlos] <i>I'm almost there.</i>

94
00:05:39,751 --> 00:05:42,293
[train whooshing]

95
00:05:42,376 --> 00:05:43,376
<i>Abort, she's a PI!</i>

96
00:05:43,959 --> 00:05:45,084
[gun firing]

97
00:05:45,751 --> 00:05:46,793
30-17, go!

98
00:05:47,584 --> 00:05:50,168
[upbeat tense music]

99
00:05:52,001 --> 00:05:53,001
Lock engage!

100
00:05:57,584 --> 00:06:00,084
[music continues]
[doorknob rattling]

101
00:06:02,501 --> 00:06:04,168
[gun firing]

102
00:06:11,126 --> 00:06:12,501
[crowd shouting, screaming]

103
00:06:12,584 --> 00:06:13,834
Oh, come on!

104
00:06:13,918 --> 00:06:15,293
You're really doing this?

105
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:18,376
Fuck me.

106
00:06:18,459 --> 00:06:20,376
[fire crackling]

107
00:06:23,251 --> 00:06:25,876
[music continues]

108
00:06:34,459 --> 00:06:37,209
[crowd shouting]

109
00:06:42,543 --> 00:06:43,543
[yells]

110
00:06:44,084 --> 00:06:45,084
[grunts]

111
00:06:46,251 --> 00:06:48,584
[music continues]
[crowd shouting]

112
00:06:57,584 --> 00:07:00,084
Dear friends, you
may fuck yourselves.

113
00:07:00,168 --> 00:07:02,459
[people grunting]

114
00:07:02,959 --> 00:07:04,376
[Aline] <i>Carlos, status.</i>

115
00:07:04,459 --> 00:07:05,751
[Carlos] <i>I'm good. Catch her.</i>

116
00:07:05,834 --> 00:07:08,251
[dark music]

117
00:07:11,043 --> 00:07:13,293
[wind whistling]

118
00:07:16,459 --> 00:07:17,751
Shut the fucking door!

119
00:07:20,084 --> 00:07:22,543
[man shouts] [grunting]

120
00:07:24,376 --> 00:07:27,001
[eerie music]

121
00:07:28,043 --> 00:07:30,459
[wind whistling]

122
00:07:30,543 --> 00:07:33,376
[grunting]

123
00:07:33,876 --> 00:07:35,209
[yelping]

124
00:07:35,293 --> 00:07:37,751
[intense music]

125
00:07:37,834 --> 00:07:39,709
[grunting]

126
00:07:44,501 --> 00:07:46,418
[grunting]

127
00:07:46,501 --> 00:07:48,751
You can't do this!
You're a robot.

128
00:07:48,834 --> 00:07:51,001
Directive seven, release.

129
00:07:57,126 --> 00:08:00,626
Shit. Shit. [grunting]

130
00:08:01,168 --> 00:08:05,751
Roberta Williams, warrant
71635, aggravated hacking.

131
00:08:07,543 --> 00:08:09,168
I'm taking you home.

132
00:08:09,834 --> 00:08:12,334
[soft tense music]

133
00:08:18,418 --> 00:08:20,001
[announcer on PA]
<i>Your attention please.</i>

134
00:08:20,084 --> 00:08:24,834
<i>Would passengers on Rocosmos
flight FC805 to L-Copernic</i>

135
00:08:24,918 --> 00:08:26,793
<i>please now proceed to gate B.</i>

136
00:08:34,126 --> 00:08:36,376
<i>Passengers of Atlas Flight 615</i>

137
00:08:36,459 --> 00:08:38,668
<i>coming from Grand La Grange,</i>

138
00:08:38,751 --> 00:08:39,584
<i>please head towards</i>

139
00:08:39,668 --> 00:08:43,168
<i>decontamination
corridors C3 and C4.</i>

140
00:08:44,751 --> 00:08:47,001
Royjacker sent you, didn't he?

141
00:08:48,418 --> 00:08:50,751
Well, that bastard
hacked my servers, okay?

142
00:08:50,834 --> 00:08:52,626
I simply returned the favor.

143
00:08:52,709 --> 00:08:55,293
[announcer on PA] <i>Welcome
to Shanghai Interconnection.</i>

144
00:08:59,126 --> 00:09:01,043
You know you're the
bad guys, right?

145
00:09:01,126 --> 00:09:03,709
I don't jailbreak the
androids, I set them free.

146
00:09:04,959 --> 00:09:07,709
We saw what happens when
they're set free of Novigrad.

147
00:09:08,084 --> 00:09:10,543
[Roberta] We don't actually
know what happened there.

148
00:09:10,626 --> 00:09:13,001
Oh yeah? I know the
robots in our unit

149
00:09:13,084 --> 00:09:15,126
turned on us and
started gunning us down.

150
00:09:16,501 --> 00:09:19,293
Wait, you were in Novigrad?

151
00:09:22,001 --> 00:09:25,584
[announcer on PA] <i>Mars Express
flight ME-187 to Noctis</i>

152
00:09:25,668 --> 00:09:27,043
<i>is now boarding.</i>

153
00:09:27,543 --> 00:09:28,834
[Carlos] Hey, that's us.

154
00:09:28,918 --> 00:09:31,584
[train whooshing]

155
00:09:39,126 --> 00:09:41,459
[inaudible dialogue]

156
00:09:52,584 --> 00:09:55,293
[seatbelt bell dinging]

157
00:09:58,918 --> 00:10:01,668
[rockets firing]

158
00:10:13,001 --> 00:10:14,709
[whooshing]

159
00:10:23,251 --> 00:10:25,834
[gentle music]

160
00:10:48,584 --> 00:10:51,959
[music continues]

161
00:11:07,209 --> 00:11:10,626
[light orchestral music]

162
00:11:33,668 --> 00:11:37,084
[music continues]

163
00:11:49,418 --> 00:11:52,043
[music continues]

164
00:11:52,126 --> 00:11:54,876
[ship rumbling]

165
00:11:57,543 --> 00:12:00,043
[engines whirring]

166
00:12:01,709 --> 00:12:03,918
[engines shutting
down] [metal clanking]

167
00:12:05,959 --> 00:12:07,668
[Aline] Well check again then.

168
00:12:07,751 --> 00:12:09,084
I don't know what to tell you.

169
00:12:09,168 --> 00:12:10,626
Warrants don't just disappear.

170
00:12:10,709 --> 00:12:12,876
Well, I mean there are
a few ways to do it.

171
00:12:13,626 --> 00:12:16,668
Sorry, I don't see a warrant
for Roberta Williams.

172
00:12:16,751 --> 00:12:18,709
You got a hard copy?

173
00:12:18,793 --> 00:12:21,043
It's at the office, accessing.

174
00:12:22,334 --> 00:12:25,251
[Aline] We've been chasing
this scumbag for three weeks.

175
00:12:26,334 --> 00:12:27,501
God da...

176
00:12:28,126 --> 00:12:29,959
It's been erased
from our database.

177
00:12:30,043 --> 00:12:30,793
[Aline] It what?

178
00:12:30,876 --> 00:12:32,584
Huh? So weird.

179
00:12:33,126 --> 00:12:34,185
I hate to be a know-it-all,

180
00:12:34,209 --> 00:12:37,584
but isn't it illegal to cuff
citizens without a warrant?

181
00:12:37,668 --> 00:12:39,293
[man] I mean, she's right.

182
00:12:39,918 --> 00:12:41,418
Oh, you're the best.

183
00:12:44,251 --> 00:12:46,876
[eerie music] [car whirring]

184
00:13:00,126 --> 00:13:02,959
[grand music]

185
00:13:20,501 --> 00:13:21,584
[Aline] <i>Hey, Beryl.</i>

186
00:13:21,668 --> 00:13:23,668
[Beryl] <i>Hi sweetie.
How was it?</i>

187
00:13:23,751 --> 00:13:26,084
[Aline] <i>Same old slum
for the unemployed.</i>

188
00:13:26,168 --> 00:13:27,959
<i>Is Chris available for our chat?</i>

189
00:13:28,043 --> 00:13:30,376
[Beryl] <i>Didn't you
know? He retired me.</i>

190
00:13:30,459 --> 00:13:31,977
- [Aline] <i>Really?</i>
- [Beryl] <i>Stay on the line,</i>

191
00:13:32,001 --> 00:13:33,459
<i>I'll transfer you
to the new one.</i>

192
00:13:33,543 --> 00:13:34,418
[Aline] <i>Are you okay?</i>

193
00:13:34,501 --> 00:13:36,834
[Beryl] <i>Oh, don't you worry.
I'm keeping plenty busy.</i>

194
00:13:36,918 --> 00:13:39,293
<i>See you soon. I'll
put you through.</i>

195
00:13:39,376 --> 00:13:41,584
[Janine] <i>Hello,
Aline. I'm Janine.</i>

196
00:13:41,668 --> 00:13:43,959
<i>Chris Royjacker is
waiting in your office.</i>

197
00:13:50,376 --> 00:13:52,209
- [Aline] Hey Chris.
<i>- How's it going?</i>

198
00:13:52,293 --> 00:13:53,668
<i>So Earth, huh?</i>

199
00:13:53,751 --> 00:13:55,126
<i>Bet it's nice to be home.</i>

200
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:56,334
It is.

201
00:13:56,418 --> 00:13:57,584
[Chris] <i>Hey, Carlos.</i>

202
00:13:57,668 --> 00:13:59,043
[Aline] Have you
read my report?

203
00:13:59,126 --> 00:14:00,168
<i>Yeah, I did.</i>

204
00:14:00,251 --> 00:14:02,084
<i>So they let Roberta
Williams go, huh?</i>

205
00:14:02,168 --> 00:14:03,918
I'll make sure
she's back in cuffs.

206
00:14:04,001 --> 00:14:05,543
<i>Forget it. Her
computer's burnt.</i>

207
00:14:05,626 --> 00:14:07,043
<i>That's all I care about.</i>

208
00:14:07,126 --> 00:14:08,543
If you don't mind filling me in,

209
00:14:08,626 --> 00:14:10,334
what kind of data did she steal?

210
00:14:10,418 --> 00:14:12,126
<i>I don't know, it
doesn't matter anymore.</i>

211
00:14:12,209 --> 00:14:13,251
<i>Just forget about it.</i>

212
00:14:13,334 --> 00:14:14,251
[woman] <i>Woo!</i>

213
00:14:14,334 --> 00:14:17,543
[Chris laughing]

214
00:14:17,626 --> 00:14:18,543
<i>Enjoy yourself.</i>

215
00:14:18,626 --> 00:14:20,418
<i>Go out, make some friends.</i>

216
00:14:20,501 --> 00:14:21,793
<i>All right, see you around.</i>

217
00:14:27,543 --> 00:14:30,501
[Aline grunting]

218
00:14:37,626 --> 00:14:40,376
[continues grunting]

219
00:14:43,543 --> 00:14:45,626
[reporter] <i>Does the
Gliese 581 solar system</i>

220
00:14:45,709 --> 00:14:48,126
<i>have a livable, just-right,
Goldilocks planet?</i>

221
00:14:48,668 --> 00:14:50,251
<i>This is the question
humanity asked</i>

222
00:14:50,334 --> 00:14:53,834
<i>the universe 53 years ago
when it sent the Ekinci probe.</i>

223
00:14:53,918 --> 00:14:55,501
<i>It's been 20 years since Ekinci</i>

224
00:14:55,584 --> 00:14:59,418
<i>dropped into orbit around
exoplanet Gliese 581D.</i>

225
00:14:59,501 --> 00:15:00,560
<i>We will soon start receiving</i>

226
00:15:00,584 --> 00:15:03,084
<i>its first data
transmissions any day now.</i>

227
00:15:03,168 --> 00:15:03,918
<i>So...</i>

228
00:15:04,001 --> 00:15:05,961
- [clears throat]
<i>- Who's tempted by the star?</i>

229
00:15:07,584 --> 00:15:10,043
Oh, don't worry, updates.
You know how they are.

230
00:15:10,126 --> 00:15:11,376
Can you do it?

231
00:15:11,459 --> 00:15:13,543
I kind of have a meeting.

232
00:15:13,626 --> 00:15:15,251
Well, it won't be much longer.

233
00:15:15,334 --> 00:15:17,251
You're fine, apart
from the hand?

234
00:15:17,334 --> 00:15:18,352
[makes "I don't know" sound]

235
00:15:18,376 --> 00:15:20,543
Your analyses show you
haven't fallen off the wagon.

236
00:15:20,626 --> 00:15:23,626
That's great. The first
three months are the hardest.

237
00:15:23,918 --> 00:15:24,918
[computer dings]

238
00:15:25,001 --> 00:15:26,126
There we go. See?

239
00:15:33,543 --> 00:15:34,543
[Aline] Mr. Chow?

240
00:15:36,043 --> 00:15:37,251
Aline Ruby.

241
00:15:37,751 --> 00:15:40,001
Oh, Carlos didn't let you in?

242
00:15:40,418 --> 00:15:43,084
Oh right, he's updating too.

243
00:15:45,543 --> 00:15:46,751
My daughter, Jun.

244
00:15:46,834 --> 00:15:48,334
We've had no news
for three days.

245
00:15:48,459 --> 00:15:51,043
The police are after
her for hacking.

246
00:15:51,126 --> 00:15:53,334
Hacking, really? What'd she do?

247
00:15:53,418 --> 00:15:56,084
[man] Jail-breaking a
school robot, they say.

248
00:15:56,168 --> 00:15:59,001
Now she's disappeared
along with her roommate.

249
00:15:59,084 --> 00:16:00,126
But hacking?

250
00:16:00,209 --> 00:16:01,501
So where do we start?

251
00:16:01,584 --> 00:16:03,418
I haven't really
done this before.

252
00:16:03,501 --> 00:16:05,209
We'll go look
through her things.

253
00:16:05,293 --> 00:16:06,793
Was she living on campus?

254
00:16:06,876 --> 00:16:08,751
Yeah, at the Alan Turing dorms.

255
00:16:08,834 --> 00:16:09,834
Computers?

256
00:16:09,876 --> 00:16:10,876
Cybernetics.

257
00:16:10,959 --> 00:16:12,709
You're a former Army man, right?

258
00:16:12,793 --> 00:16:13,793
Huh?

259
00:16:14,043 --> 00:16:14,834
No, why?

260
00:16:14,918 --> 00:16:17,209
My mistake. I was
in the infantry.

261
00:16:17,293 --> 00:16:19,876
When we met, you seemed
to click your heels.

262
00:16:19,959 --> 00:16:21,418
I didn't do it on purpose.

263
00:16:21,793 --> 00:16:23,593
[automated voice] <i>Memory
full or insufficient.</i>

264
00:16:23,834 --> 00:16:25,001
<i>Update canceled.</i>

265
00:16:26,501 --> 00:16:30,168
They force you to update and
every time I try, memory full!

266
00:16:30,418 --> 00:16:31,418
Oh, sorry.

267
00:16:31,501 --> 00:16:33,126
Carlos Rivera. Hey.

268
00:16:36,459 --> 00:16:39,376
Jun Chow, 18. Second
year cybernetic student.

269
00:16:39,459 --> 00:16:41,001
Clean record until now.

270
00:16:41,084 --> 00:16:42,918
Her parents are technicians
on a hydro farm.

271
00:16:44,209 --> 00:16:46,501
Oh, they were fired
three months back.

272
00:16:46,584 --> 00:16:48,501
Father has no military record.

273
00:16:48,584 --> 00:16:49,959
Not that I can see.

274
00:16:50,043 --> 00:16:53,501
- [robot laughing hysterically]
- [Carlos] Hey!

275
00:16:53,584 --> 00:16:55,751
Jesus, what is he drunk?

276
00:16:56,668 --> 00:16:58,501
Keep your distance,
he's been jail-broken.

277
00:16:59,001 --> 00:17:00,418
[laughing, panting]

278
00:17:00,501 --> 00:17:02,668
This is amazing.

279
00:17:03,293 --> 00:17:04,584
I have hands.

280
00:17:04,668 --> 00:17:05,834
[man] Stand back!

281
00:17:05,918 --> 00:17:08,751
[electricity crackling]
[robot gibbering]

282
00:17:09,043 --> 00:17:11,084
I need you to please move along.

283
00:17:14,293 --> 00:17:17,084
[electricity crackling]
[robot screaming]

284
00:17:20,876 --> 00:17:23,793
[traffic whooshing]

285
00:17:25,709 --> 00:17:28,168
[indistinct chattering]

286
00:17:31,834 --> 00:17:33,084
Over there.

287
00:17:33,709 --> 00:17:35,543
[man] I'm in a couple
classes with her.

288
00:17:35,626 --> 00:17:36,626
She busts her ass.

289
00:17:36,709 --> 00:17:39,043
[Aline] And her friend
who's also disappeared?

290
00:17:39,126 --> 00:17:42,668
Dominique? They're mostly
just roommates, not friends.

291
00:17:42,751 --> 00:17:44,918
[Aline] Gotcha. And
Dominique's last name?

292
00:17:45,001 --> 00:17:45,793
Viger.

293
00:17:45,876 --> 00:17:48,418
This about the
robot jail-breaking?

294
00:17:48,501 --> 00:17:49,876
[man] By giving them life,

295
00:17:49,959 --> 00:17:51,709
organic science brings
everyday objects

296
00:17:51,793 --> 00:17:54,751
into the virtuous
cycle of the ecosystem.

297
00:17:54,959 --> 00:17:57,001
It's my pleasure to
introduce Brian Jobe

298
00:17:57,084 --> 00:17:58,209
of Royjacker Industries

299
00:17:58,293 --> 00:18:00,793
to present one of
these new organics.

300
00:18:01,209 --> 00:18:02,394
This was actually the first time

301
00:18:02,418 --> 00:18:04,001
I've ever handled one myself.

302
00:18:04,084 --> 00:18:06,251
I'm not gonna lie, it
felt kind of weird.

303
00:18:06,334 --> 00:18:08,209
Brian, the texture
might need some work.

304
00:18:08,293 --> 00:18:10,251
[audience laughing]

305
00:18:10,584 --> 00:18:11,459
[man] Ladies and gentlemen,

306
00:18:11,543 --> 00:18:13,668
Royjacker Industries'
Brian Jobe.

307
00:18:13,918 --> 00:18:17,001
I mean, nothing about either
student really jumps out.

308
00:18:17,084 --> 00:18:17,834
Oh, you know what?

309
00:18:17,918 --> 00:18:20,418
I did notice Jun would
often come to class tired.

310
00:18:21,126 --> 00:18:23,501
Can't blame her though,
curriculum's tough.

311
00:18:23,584 --> 00:18:25,668
[Brian speaking indistinctly]

312
00:18:26,584 --> 00:18:27,959
Was that all you needed to know?

313
00:18:28,043 --> 00:18:29,209
Mm, what?

314
00:18:29,293 --> 00:18:30,334
Uh, mm.

315
00:18:30,418 --> 00:18:31,876
Both students disappeared.

316
00:18:31,959 --> 00:18:33,168
Could there be a common link?

317
00:18:33,251 --> 00:18:34,168
Yeah.

318
00:18:34,251 --> 00:18:35,251
No idea.

319
00:18:35,293 --> 00:18:36,709
I'm just their professor.

320
00:18:36,793 --> 00:18:39,501
I just try to teach them
Babel + and Hegel 7.

321
00:18:39,584 --> 00:18:41,043
I don't know their
personal lives.

322
00:18:41,126 --> 00:18:43,418
Oh, sorry. The dean's
mind-speaking to me.

323
00:18:43,501 --> 00:18:46,876
[Brian] What I have in my
pocket will achieve that vision.

324
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:48,209
I know it's still taught here

325
00:18:48,293 --> 00:18:50,168
that organic technology
is still purely

326
00:18:50,251 --> 00:18:51,876
in the realm of the theoretical.

327
00:18:51,959 --> 00:18:53,251
They will have you believe

328
00:18:53,334 --> 00:18:55,334
that this burgeoning
technology is too expensive

329
00:18:55,418 --> 00:18:57,376
and less efficient
than electronics.

330
00:18:57,459 --> 00:18:58,543
Not true.

331
00:18:58,626 --> 00:19:00,293
Let me introduce a little friend

332
00:19:00,376 --> 00:19:02,418
who might make you
change your mind.

333
00:19:03,084 --> 00:19:06,501
Stephanie, the first
organic personal assistant.

334
00:19:06,834 --> 00:19:08,209
The dean's on his way.

335
00:19:08,293 --> 00:19:09,584
He'll show you the recording.

336
00:19:09,793 --> 00:19:11,959
[Brian]...will have a
positive environmental impact

337
00:19:12,043 --> 00:19:15,001
in both her manufacturing
and decomposition.

338
00:19:15,084 --> 00:19:16,709
This is historic.

339
00:19:17,834 --> 00:19:20,501
[computers whirring]

340
00:19:30,584 --> 00:19:33,584
[footsteps approaching]

341
00:19:41,834 --> 00:19:43,543
I'll just fast forward a little.

342
00:19:57,084 --> 00:19:59,543
[eerie music]

343
00:20:03,626 --> 00:20:04,626
What?

344
00:20:12,126 --> 00:20:14,084
What the hell's going on?

345
00:20:14,584 --> 00:20:15,334
[screaming]

346
00:20:15,418 --> 00:20:16,778
[Carlos] She tried
to shut him off.

347
00:20:16,834 --> 00:20:18,334
The android's defending himself.

348
00:20:18,418 --> 00:20:20,168
[Aline] In breach
of directive one.

349
00:20:20,251 --> 00:20:22,293
[dean] Yes, he's clearly
been jail-broken.

350
00:20:23,293 --> 00:20:26,043
[intense music]

351
00:20:27,959 --> 00:20:28,959
[Jun yelps]

352
00:20:31,876 --> 00:20:33,043
Deactivate now!

353
00:20:33,293 --> 00:20:34,293
Oh my God.

354
00:20:44,626 --> 00:20:46,043
[music fades]

355
00:20:46,126 --> 00:20:47,326
Has this ever happened before?

356
00:20:47,376 --> 00:20:49,334
A jailbreak? No.

357
00:20:49,418 --> 00:20:51,459
Well, at least not
since I became Dean.

358
00:20:51,751 --> 00:20:53,834
I was more surprised
than anyone.

359
00:20:53,918 --> 00:20:57,043
And then when I heard reports
about gunfire in the dorm.

360
00:20:57,251 --> 00:20:58,251
Gunfire?

361
00:21:01,959 --> 00:21:03,959
[dean] Somehow no one on
the floor heard a thing,

362
00:21:04,043 --> 00:21:06,501
but it's clear a
gunfight occurred here.

363
00:21:06,584 --> 00:21:07,834
Don't touch anything.

364
00:21:07,918 --> 00:21:10,001
The police wanted me
to make sure that...

365
00:21:10,084 --> 00:21:11,584
[retching]

366
00:21:13,168 --> 00:21:15,543
I take it dorm rooms don't
always smell like that?

367
00:21:16,043 --> 00:21:17,293
Mm-mm. [groans]

368
00:21:17,459 --> 00:21:18,459
Is it bad?

369
00:21:20,376 --> 00:21:23,709
[eerie music] [flies buzzing]

370
00:21:45,918 --> 00:21:48,251
[whirring]

371
00:22:17,543 --> 00:22:20,043
[music continues]

372
00:22:26,001 --> 00:22:28,959
[flies continue buzzing]

373
00:22:53,293 --> 00:22:55,834
[distant phone ringing]

374
00:23:04,043 --> 00:23:06,126
[indistinct conversation]

375
00:23:15,668 --> 00:23:17,251
Mr. And Mrs. Viger?

376
00:23:17,709 --> 00:23:18,959
Was it you who found Dominique?

377
00:23:19,459 --> 00:23:20,293
Aline Ruby.

378
00:23:20,376 --> 00:23:22,668
Simon Gordaux, in
charge of the case.

379
00:23:22,751 --> 00:23:24,043
My condolences.

380
00:23:24,126 --> 00:23:25,876
This is Mr. Chow, Jun's father.

381
00:23:28,001 --> 00:23:30,918
I just can't unsee it,
what they did to her.

382
00:23:31,709 --> 00:23:32,709
My girl.

383
00:23:32,959 --> 00:23:33,959
[groans]

384
00:23:34,084 --> 00:23:35,876
Come on, why don't
we go sit down.

385
00:23:39,959 --> 00:23:41,102
[Aline] Recovered
from their room.

386
00:23:41,126 --> 00:23:42,543
[Simon] Our lab
techs missed this?

387
00:23:42,918 --> 00:23:45,209
At first glance it
appears homemade.

388
00:23:45,293 --> 00:23:46,959
Was your daughter
involved with drugs?

389
00:23:47,043 --> 00:23:47,959
[gasps] No.

390
00:23:48,043 --> 00:23:49,310
Or the pills might
have been Jun's,

391
00:23:49,334 --> 00:23:50,709
since they were roommates.

392
00:23:50,793 --> 00:23:53,168
Well, that's exactly what
I was telling you earlier.

393
00:23:53,251 --> 00:23:54,501
That girl didn't belong there.

394
00:23:54,584 --> 00:23:55,334
Why not?

395
00:23:55,418 --> 00:23:57,418
How in the world was
she paying her tuition?

396
00:23:57,834 --> 00:23:59,168
People like that can't afford

397
00:23:59,251 --> 00:24:01,459
the best university in Noctis.

398
00:24:01,543 --> 00:24:03,084
I knew she was trouble.

399
00:24:03,293 --> 00:24:04,709
Now if you'll excuse me.

400
00:24:05,626 --> 00:24:07,793
[whispers] Her daughter
thought Jun was a prostitute.

401
00:24:08,709 --> 00:24:10,668
Gordaux, are you
hitting on humans?

402
00:24:10,751 --> 00:24:13,918
Can't spring for
a bot? [laughing]

403
00:24:14,001 --> 00:24:16,668
Oh yeah, good one. Get
outta here, Vlasek.

404
00:24:16,751 --> 00:24:18,168
Don't you have shit to do?

405
00:24:18,251 --> 00:24:19,543
Eh, it's a joke!

406
00:24:20,001 --> 00:24:21,001
Are you new here?

407
00:24:22,209 --> 00:24:23,209
It's that obvious?

408
00:24:25,418 --> 00:24:27,334
[woman] <i>Police, seventh
district. Go ahead.</i>

409
00:24:27,793 --> 00:24:29,418
[Jun] <i>I was
attacked by a robot.</i>

410
00:24:29,501 --> 00:24:30,293
[woman] <i>Are you hurt?</i>

411
00:24:30,376 --> 00:24:33,043
[Jun] <i>No, he pushed
me down and ran away.</i>

412
00:24:33,126 --> 00:24:33,918
[woman] <i>Okay, stay put.</i>

413
00:24:34,001 --> 00:24:35,459
<i>I'll dispatch a unit your way.</i>

414
00:24:35,834 --> 00:24:37,793
- [Jun] <i>Yeah. Okay.</i>
- [Aline sniffing]

415
00:24:37,876 --> 00:24:39,543
[woman] <i>Can you
confirm your address?</i>

416
00:24:40,251 --> 00:24:43,126
My theory is the killer
intercepted this phone call,

417
00:24:43,209 --> 00:24:44,293
got there before police

418
00:24:44,376 --> 00:24:45,876
and mistook Dominique for her.

419
00:24:45,959 --> 00:24:47,084
[Aline sniffing]

420
00:24:50,251 --> 00:24:52,126
But is it even possible?

421
00:24:52,209 --> 00:24:53,959
Intercepting calls
to the police?

422
00:24:54,918 --> 00:24:55,959
Whatcha think, Gilbert?

423
00:24:56,043 --> 00:24:57,084
[Gilbert] <i>No, Inspector.</i>

424
00:24:57,168 --> 00:24:58,543
<i>Our communication protocols</i>

425
00:24:58,626 --> 00:25:00,543
<i>make that kind of
hacking impossible.</i>

426
00:25:00,834 --> 00:25:03,834
[Aline] Oh, so that's
what I was smelling.

427
00:25:03,918 --> 00:25:05,251
You have an organic?

428
00:25:05,334 --> 00:25:06,668
[Gilbert] <i>Pardon the smell.</i>

429
00:25:07,001 --> 00:25:09,709
Gamma Amilanidridase Benzoate.

430
00:25:09,793 --> 00:25:10,668
Ever heard of it?

431
00:25:10,751 --> 00:25:12,918
[Gilbert] <i>That exact
molecule isn't listed,</i>

432
00:25:13,001 --> 00:25:14,584
<i>but its makeup
indicates it's likely</i>

433
00:25:14,668 --> 00:25:16,168
<i>a psychoactive compound.</i>

434
00:25:16,251 --> 00:25:17,251
[Aline] A drug?

435
00:25:17,293 --> 00:25:18,793
Certainly gives us a motive.

436
00:25:18,876 --> 00:25:19,793
Thanks, thingy.

437
00:25:19,876 --> 00:25:22,209
[Gilbert] <i>You're welcome,
and my name is Gilbert.</i>

438
00:25:22,376 --> 00:25:24,751
I also checked into Jun
Chow's bank accounts.

439
00:25:24,834 --> 00:25:27,209
She's been paying big sums
of money to her parents.

440
00:25:27,293 --> 00:25:28,918
Because they were both laid off.

441
00:25:29,001 --> 00:25:30,293
Where'd it come from?

442
00:25:30,501 --> 00:25:32,793
Untraceable, like
dirty money for sure.

443
00:25:32,876 --> 00:25:34,959
Well that would fit
with prostitution.

444
00:25:35,043 --> 00:25:36,685
[Gilbert] <i>That's quite
an interesting lead.</i>

445
00:25:36,709 --> 00:25:38,959
Keep your opinions
in your jar, thingy.

446
00:25:39,043 --> 00:25:41,418
[Gilbert] <i>I apologize,
and my name is Gilbert.</i>

447
00:25:55,209 --> 00:25:56,834
[doorbell ringing]

448
00:25:56,918 --> 00:25:58,168
[woman] Hey, can I hel...

449
00:25:59,043 --> 00:26:00,043
Hi Carol.

450
00:26:01,959 --> 00:26:04,459
I thought these might
look nice in your garden.

451
00:26:04,751 --> 00:26:05,751
They're from Earth.

452
00:26:07,209 --> 00:26:08,626
Leave or I'll call the judge.

453
00:26:08,959 --> 00:26:11,418
I haven't seen her in
two years. Come on.

454
00:26:11,709 --> 00:26:12,751
[sighs]

455
00:26:12,876 --> 00:26:14,543
[girl] Mommy, who is it?

456
00:26:14,793 --> 00:26:16,126
[stammers] No one.

457
00:26:16,209 --> 00:26:18,251
Philip will be home
soon, you should go.

458
00:26:18,334 --> 00:26:20,001
You can't stop me seeing her.

459
00:26:20,168 --> 00:26:21,584
Oh yeah? And what if I don't?

460
00:26:21,668 --> 00:26:22,668
You'll hit me?

461
00:26:23,293 --> 00:26:25,793
- [sirens wailing]
- [Carol] Ah. See? Just in time.

462
00:26:29,834 --> 00:26:30,834
Carol.

463
00:26:33,251 --> 00:26:35,126
Relax, Phillip.
I was just going.

464
00:26:35,959 --> 00:26:37,043
You okay, babe?

465
00:26:37,126 --> 00:26:38,209
I am. Thank you.

466
00:26:38,293 --> 00:26:40,876
[dog barking]

467
00:26:43,709 --> 00:26:45,709
[Phillip] It's okay,
you're safe now.

468
00:26:45,793 --> 00:26:46,793
Don't be scared.

469
00:26:53,168 --> 00:26:54,168
[Phillip] Hey!

470
00:26:54,793 --> 00:26:55,626
[vase breaking]

471
00:26:55,709 --> 00:26:56,709
You forgot something.

472
00:27:02,376 --> 00:27:03,834
You piece of shit!

473
00:27:03,918 --> 00:27:06,334
[dramatic music] [grunting]

474
00:27:06,459 --> 00:27:08,001
What are you trying to do, man?

475
00:27:08,376 --> 00:27:09,709
Come in, leave him.

476
00:27:12,043 --> 00:27:13,334
[grunting]

477
00:27:15,459 --> 00:27:16,709
[door closing]

478
00:27:17,209 --> 00:27:19,793
[rain pattering]

479
00:27:25,668 --> 00:27:27,418
[phone ringing]

480
00:27:29,459 --> 00:27:30,209
Yeah.

481
00:27:30,293 --> 00:27:31,668
[Simon] <i>Hi, it's
Inspector Gordaux.</i>

482
00:27:31,751 --> 00:27:32,584
[Aline] Mm-hm.

483
00:27:32,668 --> 00:27:34,584
[Simon] <i>Uh, we found
the android Jun hacked.</i>

484
00:27:34,668 --> 00:27:37,126
<i>I'm heading over now.
You want to come?</i>

485
00:27:37,376 --> 00:27:38,418
[Aline grunts softly]

486
00:27:40,001 --> 00:27:42,584
[wind whistling]

487
00:27:57,251 --> 00:27:59,459
[Simon] The first
colonists lived down here?

488
00:27:59,543 --> 00:28:02,126
[grimaces] I definitely
don't think I could have.

489
00:28:02,209 --> 00:28:04,293
We're a lot better off under
the domes if you ask me.

490
00:28:04,376 --> 00:28:05,751
- Am I right?
- Mm-hm.

491
00:28:06,709 --> 00:28:10,584
So anyway, you seeing anyone?

492
00:28:10,668 --> 00:28:11,793
There they are.

493
00:28:13,709 --> 00:28:16,626
[woman shouting indistinctly]

494
00:28:17,209 --> 00:28:19,376
Ah, so nice to talk to people,

495
00:28:19,459 --> 00:28:21,001
even if they're robots.

496
00:28:21,084 --> 00:28:23,543
People, they just don't
talk to each other anymore.

497
00:28:23,626 --> 00:28:25,918
Well, we talked to him,
but he never said much.

498
00:28:26,001 --> 00:28:28,459
You know, the guy was a
little crazy if you ask me.

499
00:28:28,543 --> 00:28:30,751
He was always lugging
all this crap around.

500
00:28:30,834 --> 00:28:33,918
You know the type, and that
was his spot over there.

501
00:28:34,001 --> 00:28:35,209
[woman continues indistinctly]

502
00:28:35,293 --> 00:28:36,293
[cops laughing]

503
00:28:36,376 --> 00:28:38,834
Hey, I'd love to
hear what's so funny.

504
00:28:39,043 --> 00:28:40,584
Oh, sorry.

505
00:28:40,668 --> 00:28:41,668
Here's an invite.

506
00:28:42,543 --> 00:28:43,543
[Aline] Thanks.

507
00:28:44,376 --> 00:28:46,168
<i>Yeah, at least three.</i>

508
00:28:46,251 --> 00:28:48,084
<i>You see that? He put
up a fight at least.</i>

509
00:28:48,168 --> 00:28:49,543
<i>You analyze the blood?</i>

510
00:28:49,626 --> 00:28:51,751
<i>Yeah, check it out.</i>

511
00:28:51,834 --> 00:28:54,293
[Aline] <i>I saw this in
the army, nano sutures.</i>

512
00:28:54,376 --> 00:28:56,626
<i>It looks like we've got
an augmented on our hands.</i>

513
00:28:56,709 --> 00:28:58,669
[man] <i>Well, there were
three individuals involved.</i>

514
00:28:58,751 --> 00:28:59,834
[man 2] <i>Three augmented?</i>

515
00:28:59,918 --> 00:29:01,751
<i>Who'd send a squad
of augmented humans</i>

516
00:29:01,834 --> 00:29:03,543
<i>to destroy some
worthless android?</i>

517
00:29:05,001 --> 00:29:07,543
Hey! You might want to
take a look at this.

518
00:29:09,793 --> 00:29:12,793
Your robot was pretty busy
redecorating the place.

519
00:29:12,959 --> 00:29:15,834
[ambient music]

520
00:29:28,584 --> 00:29:31,251
[soft mysterious music]

521
00:29:44,043 --> 00:29:47,126
[dark music]

522
00:30:14,501 --> 00:30:15,793
[Carlos] <i>A spaceship?</i>

523
00:30:15,876 --> 00:30:16,918
[Aline] <i>Yes siree.</i>

524
00:30:17,001 --> 00:30:18,801
<i>The android was building
it with whatever bits</i>

525
00:30:18,876 --> 00:30:20,126
<i>and bolts it could salvage.</i>

526
00:30:20,209 --> 00:30:22,209
<i>I mean, you should have
seen the guys' faces.</i>

527
00:30:22,293 --> 00:30:24,653
<i>The tech said it had essentially
single-handedly constructed</i>

528
00:30:24,709 --> 00:30:27,001
<i>a sort of modified
Silverbury fighter.</i>

529
00:30:27,084 --> 00:30:29,543
[Carlos] <i>What did Jun
Chow do to that Android?</i>

530
00:30:30,418 --> 00:30:31,685
<i>And wouldn't the dome
have kept something</i>

531
00:30:31,709 --> 00:30:33,293
<i>that massive from getting out?</i>

532
00:30:33,376 --> 00:30:34,626
[Aline] <i>Yeah, you'd think,</i>

533
00:30:34,709 --> 00:30:36,918
<i>but actually the ship
was just narrow enough</i>

534
00:30:37,001 --> 00:30:38,921
<i>to get through a vent
during a carbon extraction.</i>

535
00:30:39,334 --> 00:30:40,209
[Carlos] I don't get it.

536
00:30:40,293 --> 00:30:42,043
Why would someone
build a spaceship?

537
00:30:42,126 --> 00:30:44,001
Wild guess but, to go to space.

538
00:30:44,084 --> 00:30:45,709
[upbeat electronic
music playing]

539
00:30:45,793 --> 00:30:48,043
Oh, by the way, how did
things go with Carol?

540
00:30:48,626 --> 00:30:51,376
We talked and I
saw my little girl.

541
00:30:51,459 --> 00:30:53,001
[Aline] Hey, there you go.

542
00:30:53,751 --> 00:30:56,418
[man] Sir, sir, wait!

543
00:30:56,751 --> 00:30:58,084
Can you show me
that photo again?

544
00:30:58,668 --> 00:31:01,001
[car whirring]

545
00:31:05,001 --> 00:31:07,751
[muffled music]

546
00:31:23,709 --> 00:31:26,209
[upbeat music playing]

547
00:31:26,293 --> 00:31:27,293
[crowd member whistles]

548
00:31:29,876 --> 00:31:31,793
[crowd cheering]

549
00:31:38,709 --> 00:31:40,043
[inaudible dialogue]

550
00:31:45,668 --> 00:31:46,876
Go to thermal vision.

551
00:31:50,459 --> 00:31:52,334
[Aline] <i>Not one
prostitute is human.</i>

552
00:31:52,418 --> 00:31:54,709
[Carlos] <i>Yeah, I guess
the guy was wrong.</i>

553
00:31:54,793 --> 00:31:56,293
[Aline] Hey, excuse me.

554
00:31:56,376 --> 00:31:58,668
Do you have any
human prostitutes?

555
00:31:58,751 --> 00:32:01,543
Sorry, nothing but
synthetics here, I'm afraid.

556
00:32:01,626 --> 00:32:03,751
Our hosts and hostesses
are all backups,

557
00:32:03,834 --> 00:32:06,876
but we do consider
ourselves 100 percent human.

558
00:32:06,959 --> 00:32:08,126
Wouldn't you agree, sir?

559
00:32:08,209 --> 00:32:10,751
We heard this student
was working here.

560
00:32:15,959 --> 00:32:18,501
[music continues muffled]

561
00:32:22,668 --> 00:32:24,209
[door opening]

562
00:32:43,501 --> 00:32:44,501
Jun Chow?

563
00:32:47,168 --> 00:32:48,168
[shouts]

564
00:32:49,251 --> 00:32:50,168
[screams]

565
00:32:50,251 --> 00:32:51,251
Let me go.

566
00:32:52,501 --> 00:32:54,876
[running footsteps
receding] [Jun sighs]

567
00:33:07,709 --> 00:33:08,709
[Aline] Carlos?

568
00:33:10,543 --> 00:33:13,459
You know it isn't nice
to cut people's arms off.

569
00:33:22,418 --> 00:33:23,810
Do you know how her
parents are doing?

570
00:33:23,834 --> 00:33:27,251
Well I only saw your father,
but yeah, he's a strong man.

571
00:33:28,376 --> 00:33:29,918
You do realize it's a crime

572
00:33:30,001 --> 00:33:31,459
to have a backup
while still alive.

573
00:33:31,543 --> 00:33:34,084
Do you know how much
school costs these days?

574
00:33:34,168 --> 00:33:35,543
My parents got laid off.

575
00:33:35,626 --> 00:33:38,751
I had another job, but I
just got so overwhelmed.

576
00:33:38,834 --> 00:33:41,168
Do you have any idea
who's after you?

577
00:33:41,543 --> 00:33:42,834
Uh, the police?

578
00:33:43,334 --> 00:33:45,918
Yeah, Dominique was
killed by a cop.

579
00:33:46,001 --> 00:33:47,043
Fake cop?

580
00:33:47,918 --> 00:33:50,418
And in the lab, what did
you do to that robot?

581
00:33:50,793 --> 00:33:52,876
Yeah, I have no idea.

582
00:33:52,959 --> 00:33:54,060
[Carlos] We saw the recording.

583
00:33:54,084 --> 00:33:55,793
Whatever you did
drove him insane.

584
00:33:55,876 --> 00:33:56,668
[Jun] What do you mean?

585
00:33:56,751 --> 00:33:58,668
[Aline] He started
building a spaceship.

586
00:33:58,876 --> 00:34:00,001
What? No way.

587
00:34:00,251 --> 00:34:02,293
[Carlos] Oh yeah, a
15 meter launcher.

588
00:34:02,376 --> 00:34:03,560
Even our techies were impressed

589
00:34:03,584 --> 00:34:05,668
by what your robot friend
managed to cobble together.

590
00:34:05,751 --> 00:34:06,543
[Aline] Carlos, the door!

591
00:34:06,626 --> 00:34:08,168
[upbeat tense music]

592
00:34:08,251 --> 00:34:09,251
[yelps]

593
00:34:17,084 --> 00:34:18,084
[gasps]

594
00:34:20,376 --> 00:34:21,418
[gasping]

595
00:34:21,834 --> 00:34:23,834
[running footsteps receding]

596
00:34:25,834 --> 00:34:26,834
The service exit!

597
00:34:27,793 --> 00:34:29,793
[music continues]

598
00:34:33,793 --> 00:34:34,793
Hey.

599
00:34:35,168 --> 00:34:36,168
[androids shout]

600
00:34:38,668 --> 00:34:39,876
[Aline]That way!

601
00:34:43,793 --> 00:34:45,168
[car starting]

602
00:34:48,543 --> 00:34:49,543
That's ours.

603
00:34:53,959 --> 00:34:55,668
[gun firing] [Jun screams]

604
00:34:56,668 --> 00:34:57,543
[gasps]

605
00:34:57,626 --> 00:35:00,168
[low tense music]

606
00:35:01,959 --> 00:35:04,626
[engine starting]
[car whirring]

607
00:35:12,293 --> 00:35:14,251
[somber music]

608
00:35:16,584 --> 00:35:19,876
[sirens wailing]

609
00:35:38,209 --> 00:35:40,584
[music fades]
[indistinct chattering]

610
00:35:40,668 --> 00:35:42,834
[soft jazz music playing]

611
00:35:44,043 --> 00:35:45,683
[automated voice]
<i>Sobriety mode activated.</i>

612
00:35:47,334 --> 00:35:48,709
Yeah, yeah. Turn it off.

613
00:35:48,793 --> 00:35:49,584
[automated voice] <i>Do you confirm</i>

614
00:35:49,668 --> 00:35:51,751
<i>the deactivation
of sobriety mode?</i>

615
00:35:52,626 --> 00:35:53,626
Yes.

616
00:35:57,834 --> 00:35:59,293
[music continues]

617
00:35:59,376 --> 00:36:01,209
[indistinct chattering]

618
00:36:20,376 --> 00:36:21,959
But it wasn't even him.

619
00:36:22,043 --> 00:36:23,043
[all laughing]

620
00:36:26,418 --> 00:36:28,584
[funky electronic music playing]

621
00:36:32,168 --> 00:36:34,251
[woman] Not sure
what I've got left.

622
00:36:34,709 --> 00:36:35,709
What year'd you die?

623
00:36:42,293 --> 00:36:44,168
You're lucky I
never toss anything.

624
00:36:44,709 --> 00:36:46,084
Let's see how bad it is.

625
00:36:47,918 --> 00:36:49,376
Five years ago.

626
00:36:49,459 --> 00:36:51,418
Nine for me, cancer of...

627
00:36:51,793 --> 00:36:53,418
something I no longer have.

628
00:36:53,501 --> 00:36:54,584
And you?

629
00:36:54,668 --> 00:36:56,918
They never found my body.

630
00:36:57,001 --> 00:36:59,043
I was killed during the
Novigrad Insurrection.

631
00:37:00,543 --> 00:37:01,751
Do you have family?

632
00:37:02,334 --> 00:37:03,209
Yeah, a daughter.

633
00:37:03,293 --> 00:37:05,959
But my wife and I aren't really
in a great place right now.

634
00:37:06,043 --> 00:37:07,084
[woman] You're in luck.

635
00:37:07,168 --> 00:37:08,626
The socket seems intact.

636
00:37:10,001 --> 00:37:11,084
There you are.

637
00:37:11,376 --> 00:37:13,084
So the change was
too much for her?

638
00:37:13,168 --> 00:37:15,584
[Carlos] No, we were already
separated when I died.

639
00:37:16,418 --> 00:37:18,001
I was violent back then.

640
00:37:21,043 --> 00:37:22,519
[woman] We backups meet
every Wednesday night

641
00:37:22,543 --> 00:37:24,501
just to talk,
support each other.

642
00:37:24,793 --> 00:37:27,834
If you're ever feeling down,
don't be afraid to swing by.

643
00:37:29,293 --> 00:37:31,334
[upbeat jazz music]

644
00:37:31,418 --> 00:37:32,168
[professor] Me, no.

645
00:37:32,251 --> 00:37:35,168
Relationships are a pain, and
always get so complicated.

646
00:37:35,251 --> 00:37:38,209
I'm done with real women, I
just don't have the patience.

647
00:37:38,293 --> 00:37:41,168
If my synthetic busts my
balls, I can turn her off.

648
00:37:43,543 --> 00:37:44,959
Oh yeah.

649
00:37:45,043 --> 00:37:47,418
[slurring] Have you seen
these on campus before?

650
00:37:47,501 --> 00:37:49,126
They're apparently homemade.

651
00:37:49,209 --> 00:37:50,626
Oh, you mean gammas?

652
00:37:50,709 --> 00:37:52,459
Yeah, they've been
around for a few weeks.

653
00:37:52,543 --> 00:37:56,626
It's an experimental molecule
to boost your memory.

654
00:37:56,709 --> 00:37:58,251
I hear they'll use
it for studying.

655
00:37:59,876 --> 00:38:03,043
Oh sorry, I have
a call. Hey Beryl.

656
00:38:03,126 --> 00:38:05,793
[Beryl] <i>I heard what
happened. Are you okay?</i>

657
00:38:05,876 --> 00:38:07,459
Don't you go anywhere, you.

658
00:38:08,876 --> 00:38:11,584
Wait, no, Mom! I think
the issue's on my side.

659
00:38:11,668 --> 00:38:12,668
Gimme a sec.

660
00:38:17,584 --> 00:38:19,293
All right, can you
hear me now, Mom?

661
00:38:19,376 --> 00:38:20,584
Mom! Mom?

662
00:38:20,668 --> 00:38:23,293
[Aline, slurring] <i>I talked
to the girl's father.</i>

663
00:38:23,376 --> 00:38:26,418
<i>He... asked me to stop
the investigation.</i>

664
00:38:26,501 --> 00:38:29,876
<i>But</i>... [giggles]
<i>Whoopsie.</i> [laughs]

665
00:38:29,959 --> 00:38:30,876
[Beryl] <i>Have you
been drinking?</i>

666
00:38:30,959 --> 00:38:33,584
[Aline] <i>I mean</i>... [buzzes
lips] <i>Anything's possible.</i>

667
00:38:33,668 --> 00:38:36,043
[Beryl] <i>Ugh, and after all
you went through to quit.</i>

668
00:38:36,584 --> 00:38:38,209
<i>Well, no one's perfect.</i>

669
00:38:38,293 --> 00:38:39,959
<i>It's just a little slip up.</i>

670
00:38:40,209 --> 00:38:42,834
<i>We all struggle with
our demons, that's life.</i>

671
00:38:43,209 --> 00:38:45,168
<i>But may I give you some advice?</i>

672
00:38:45,293 --> 00:38:47,293
[Aline] <i>Yeah, sure
thing. Hit me.</i>

673
00:38:47,376 --> 00:38:50,709
[Beryl] <i>Finish your drink,
go home and sleep it off.</i>

674
00:38:50,793 --> 00:38:51,918
<i>Can you do that?</i>

675
00:38:52,001 --> 00:38:53,126
[door buzzer rings]

676
00:38:57,793 --> 00:38:58,793
[door shuts]

677
00:39:01,084 --> 00:39:02,084
She's in here.

678
00:39:10,584 --> 00:39:13,126
[laughing]

679
00:39:13,543 --> 00:39:14,584
[Aline groans]

680
00:39:15,126 --> 00:39:16,966
- [Carlos] I'll take you home.
- [Aline groans]

681
00:39:17,293 --> 00:39:21,584
[Aline]Three months,
11 days and 17 hours.

682
00:39:21,668 --> 00:39:23,959
Hey, that's my new high score!

683
00:39:24,043 --> 00:39:25,459
[Carlos]This was a bad idea.

684
00:39:25,543 --> 00:39:29,001
[Aline] Geez. Death
made you so boring.

685
00:39:29,084 --> 00:39:30,584
Can you blame me for drinking?

686
00:39:30,668 --> 00:39:31,828
[Carlos] I'm not really dead.

687
00:39:31,876 --> 00:39:32,959
[Aline] You're dead.

688
00:39:33,043 --> 00:39:35,584
80 percent sure your
head never used to float.

689
00:39:37,876 --> 00:39:40,876
[Mrs. Chow] And the day for
me will be like the night.

690
00:39:41,168 --> 00:39:43,959
I shall see neither
the gold of twilight

691
00:39:44,043 --> 00:39:45,501
nor the far off sails

692
00:39:45,584 --> 00:39:47,293
- approaching Harfleur.
- [phone ringing]

693
00:39:47,626 --> 00:39:51,168
[Mrs. Chow] And when I arrive,
I shall place on your grave...

694
00:39:51,251 --> 00:39:52,251
Look at Mr. Chow.

695
00:39:52,334 --> 00:39:55,001
[Mrs. Chow]...green holly
and a flower [indistinct].

696
00:39:55,959 --> 00:39:59,209
[Aline] Am I still drunk or
did he shrink since last time?

697
00:40:09,834 --> 00:40:11,084
My condolences.

698
00:40:11,168 --> 00:40:11,918
Thanks.

699
00:40:12,001 --> 00:40:14,834
Aline Ruby, my
partner, Carlos Rivera.

700
00:40:14,918 --> 00:40:16,459
Condolences.

701
00:40:16,543 --> 00:40:18,459
Have you and I ever met before?

702
00:40:19,668 --> 00:40:20,959
- [phone ringing]
- No.

703
00:40:24,376 --> 00:40:26,209
[Aline] <i>Chris, sorry. I'm busy.</i>

704
00:40:26,293 --> 00:40:27,293
[Chris] <i>We need to talk.</i>

705
00:40:27,334 --> 00:40:29,168
[Aline] <i>Not a great time, later?</i>

706
00:40:29,251 --> 00:40:31,334
[Chris] <i>Sure, come
by the house tonight.</i>

707
00:40:31,418 --> 00:40:32,459
<i>I'm throwing a party.</i>

708
00:40:32,751 --> 00:40:33,751
[headset beeps]

709
00:40:36,293 --> 00:40:39,251
[machine rumbling]

710
00:40:39,334 --> 00:40:41,126
[Aline] We knew
augmenteds were involved.

711
00:40:41,209 --> 00:40:43,459
[Carlos] We couldn't know one
would impersonate her dad.

712
00:40:43,543 --> 00:40:45,376
But I clocked he
was ex-military.

713
00:40:45,459 --> 00:40:47,126
Oh, should have trusted my gut.

714
00:40:52,834 --> 00:40:54,376
It all started with
the jail-breaking

715
00:40:54,459 --> 00:40:55,709
at the university.

716
00:40:56,001 --> 00:40:58,251
We're useless with cybernetics.

717
00:40:58,334 --> 00:40:59,668
Who knows their shit?

718
00:41:00,209 --> 00:41:01,644
If I could still
get upset right now,

719
00:41:01,668 --> 00:41:04,334
old me would've slapped you
and that flask outta your mouth

720
00:41:04,418 --> 00:41:06,668
and reminded you we
failed our mission.

721
00:41:10,334 --> 00:41:11,626
[Aline exhaling]

722
00:41:13,543 --> 00:41:14,876
Come on, Carlos.

723
00:41:14,959 --> 00:41:17,293
Who knows someone
who knows something?

724
00:41:18,126 --> 00:41:19,334
Cesarsky?

725
00:41:19,418 --> 00:41:20,418
Deleval?

726
00:41:20,793 --> 00:41:23,251
No, we need an expert hacker.

727
00:41:25,043 --> 00:41:26,168
I can think of someone.

728
00:41:28,293 --> 00:41:30,293
[Aline] <i>Oh no.</i>

729
00:41:38,251 --> 00:41:39,251
Hmm.

730
00:41:39,418 --> 00:41:41,418
If you think I'd
ever work for you,

731
00:41:41,501 --> 00:41:43,459
you're more delusional
than I thought.

732
00:41:43,959 --> 00:41:45,001
You've met LEM.

733
00:41:45,376 --> 00:41:47,084
His backup doesn't remember you.

734
00:41:47,376 --> 00:41:49,293
LEM, this is Carlos.

735
00:41:49,376 --> 00:41:51,459
He killed you last week.

736
00:41:51,709 --> 00:41:53,793
If he attacks, throw
him in the compactor.

737
00:41:53,876 --> 00:41:55,418
[LEM] Yeah, sure. Hello.

738
00:41:56,043 --> 00:41:58,668
[Roberta] Jail-broken
robots, I swear.

739
00:41:58,751 --> 00:42:01,293
Getting high and
screwing all day long.

740
00:42:02,043 --> 00:42:03,793
Is there any chance
you've ever seen one

741
00:42:03,876 --> 00:42:05,876
paint frescoes or
build a spaceship?

742
00:42:08,793 --> 00:42:10,209
[Roberta] Was this
video doctored?

743
00:42:10,293 --> 00:42:12,043
[Carlos] I don't think so. Why?

744
00:42:12,709 --> 00:42:14,144
[Roberta] This wasn't
a jail-breaking.

745
00:42:14,168 --> 00:42:16,876
For that, you just pop
the hood and solder

746
00:42:16,959 --> 00:42:18,001
and melt a few things.

747
00:42:18,084 --> 00:42:20,418
But this, it's a takeover.

748
00:42:20,501 --> 00:42:22,543
I've tried to write a
program to do that for years,

749
00:42:22,626 --> 00:42:24,584
but I was never
able to manage it.

750
00:42:24,668 --> 00:42:26,834
[Carlos] So how is that
different from jail-breaking?

751
00:42:26,918 --> 00:42:29,293
Well, with a takeover,
you can order the machine

752
00:42:29,376 --> 00:42:31,043
to do anything
you want it to do.

753
00:42:31,126 --> 00:42:32,352
[Carlos] Then it's
not being freed.

754
00:42:32,376 --> 00:42:33,584
You could do that.

755
00:42:33,668 --> 00:42:36,584
Like you could order it to
erase all its directives

756
00:42:36,668 --> 00:42:38,459
and take its freedom
if you wanted.

757
00:42:38,668 --> 00:42:40,626
It'd be instantaneous
jail-breaking.

758
00:42:40,709 --> 00:42:42,251
And get this, that freedom

759
00:42:42,334 --> 00:42:44,459
would be transmissible
between robots.

760
00:42:44,543 --> 00:42:46,668
The holy grail of emancipators.

761
00:42:46,751 --> 00:42:49,918
[Carlos] Okay, so it depends on
the order you give to the robot.

762
00:42:50,001 --> 00:42:50,751
Right.

763
00:42:50,834 --> 00:42:52,876
If for instance, I used
a takeover to tell you

764
00:42:52,959 --> 00:42:54,352
to kill your buddy
Aline, you'd do it,

765
00:42:54,376 --> 00:42:56,376
convinced it was
your own great idea.

766
00:42:56,751 --> 00:42:59,168
[Carlos] So you're saying
that girl, some student,

767
00:42:59,459 --> 00:43:01,126
did what you never
managed to do?

768
00:43:01,501 --> 00:43:03,293
[scoffing] No, rude.

769
00:43:03,376 --> 00:43:05,626
It was that bastard
who screwed me over.

770
00:43:05,709 --> 00:43:07,876
[Carlos] Does this ba...
fellow have a name?

771
00:43:11,084 --> 00:43:14,376
[indistinct chattering]

772
00:43:24,209 --> 00:43:26,834
[Beryl] <i>Ah, I see you
followed my advice.</i>

773
00:43:26,918 --> 00:43:31,084
Hey Beryl, you can't judge,
you've never felt thirsty.

774
00:43:31,918 --> 00:43:33,709
What is that nightmare?

775
00:43:34,334 --> 00:43:35,852
[Beryl] <i>Chris hopes
to replace soldiers</i>

776
00:43:35,876 --> 00:43:37,876
<i>with these organic
creatures from hell.</i>

777
00:43:37,959 --> 00:43:39,626
Are there customers
already lined up

778
00:43:39,709 --> 00:43:40,793
for these meat machines?

779
00:43:40,876 --> 00:43:42,584
[Beryl] <i>It's building slowly.</i>

780
00:43:42,668 --> 00:43:45,084
<i>Obviously don't tell
the shareholders.</i>

781
00:43:45,168 --> 00:43:46,251
Wow, are sales that bad?

782
00:43:46,334 --> 00:43:49,043
[Beryl] <i>I'm afraid that
information is confidential.</i>

783
00:43:49,376 --> 00:43:50,543
[chuckles]

784
00:44:18,918 --> 00:44:20,918
[Janine] <i>Delighted
to meet you, Aline.</i>

785
00:44:21,001 --> 00:44:24,209
<i>I'm Janine, Beryl's replacement.</i>

786
00:44:24,293 --> 00:44:27,418
Here I thought progress moved
towards miniaturization.

787
00:44:27,668 --> 00:44:29,793
[Janine] <i>My designer
likes to dream big.</i>

788
00:44:29,876 --> 00:44:31,459
- [phone rings]
- [Aline] <i>Hey, Carlos.</i>

789
00:44:31,543 --> 00:44:33,501
[Carlos] <i>So you're
not gonna like this.</i>

790
00:44:33,584 --> 00:44:34,334
[Aline] <i>What do you got?</i>

791
00:44:34,418 --> 00:44:35,978
[Carlos] <i>It was Chris
who was after Jun.</i>

792
00:44:36,043 --> 00:44:37,584
<i>He ordered her assassination.</i>

793
00:44:37,751 --> 00:44:39,168
[door opens]

794
00:44:40,709 --> 00:44:42,209
Oh, what a circus.

795
00:44:42,293 --> 00:44:43,876
[Aline] <i>He's here.
I've gotta go.</i>

796
00:44:43,959 --> 00:44:45,293
[Carlos] <i>Be careful.</i>

797
00:44:45,668 --> 00:44:46,751
Hey, Chris.

798
00:44:50,126 --> 00:44:51,459
How you doing?

799
00:44:51,543 --> 00:44:54,168
Wait, you're ahead of
me. Let me catch up.

800
00:44:56,084 --> 00:44:57,376
You're off the wagon?

801
00:44:58,751 --> 00:45:00,084
Well then, to us.

802
00:45:01,626 --> 00:45:02,959
[Aline] You retired Beryl.

803
00:45:03,043 --> 00:45:05,418
[Chris] I did. We
gotta keep improving.

804
00:45:05,501 --> 00:45:07,584
Plus she was becoming
the morality police

805
00:45:07,668 --> 00:45:08,709
in her old age,

806
00:45:08,793 --> 00:45:10,126
but she's our Beryl.

807
00:45:10,209 --> 00:45:12,376
You know? I'm not
gonna unplug her.

808
00:45:13,376 --> 00:45:15,709
Anyway, I wanted to come
here to talk to you about...

809
00:45:15,793 --> 00:45:17,376
Dropping my investigation?

810
00:45:19,626 --> 00:45:20,876
I adore you, Aline,

811
00:45:21,251 --> 00:45:23,251
and I can't say that
about many people.

812
00:45:23,334 --> 00:45:24,668
Please, sit down.

813
00:45:28,376 --> 00:45:30,418
When did you start
ordering murders?

814
00:45:30,876 --> 00:45:32,584
[water bubbling]

815
00:45:32,709 --> 00:45:34,959
I didn't give the order
to liquidate Miss Chow.

816
00:45:35,043 --> 00:45:36,293
Then who did?

817
00:45:36,376 --> 00:45:37,560
I'll tell you what
you wanna know,

818
00:45:37,584 --> 00:45:39,543
but for the next
three days, look away,

819
00:45:39,626 --> 00:45:40,418
keep your head down.

820
00:45:40,501 --> 00:45:41,793
Chris, what's going on?

821
00:45:41,876 --> 00:45:43,584
Stop asking
questions. I told you.

822
00:45:43,751 --> 00:45:45,709
Why'd the school
destroy the robot?

823
00:45:45,918 --> 00:45:48,918
[inhales deeply]
[low tense music]

824
00:45:54,584 --> 00:45:56,626
You shouldn't have
started drinking again.

825
00:45:57,126 --> 00:45:58,376
It's bad for your health.

826
00:46:02,293 --> 00:46:04,918
[sinister music]

827
00:46:15,876 --> 00:46:17,769
[Carlos] <i>Roberta Williams
had been trying for years</i>

828
00:46:17,793 --> 00:46:19,918
<i>to develop a software
known as a takeover</i>

829
00:46:20,001 --> 00:46:22,376
<i>that would give the user
total control of a robot.</i>

830
00:46:22,834 --> 00:46:25,543
<i>Royjacker's agents hacked her
servers to steal her work.</i>

831
00:46:25,626 --> 00:46:27,376
<i>With their resources
and deep pockets,</i>

832
00:46:27,459 --> 00:46:28,793
<i>they finished the job.</i>

833
00:46:28,876 --> 00:46:31,251
<i>Roberta had proof and was
gonna reveal everything.</i>

834
00:46:31,334 --> 00:46:32,852
[Aline] <i>And that's why
he sent us to Earth</i>

835
00:46:32,876 --> 00:46:33,876
<i>to chase her down.</i>

836
00:46:33,959 --> 00:46:36,501
[Carlos] <i>This takeover was the
program Jun used on the robot,</i>

837
00:46:36,584 --> 00:46:39,043
<i>with some additional tweaks
by Royjacker's techs.</i>

838
00:46:39,126 --> 00:46:41,668
[Aline] <i>That program was
what drove the robots nuts.</i>

839
00:46:42,084 --> 00:46:44,293
<i>That's why the university
had to destroy it.</i>

840
00:46:51,376 --> 00:46:53,334
Do we know what
it does to robots?

841
00:46:53,418 --> 00:46:54,209
[Carlos] No.

842
00:46:54,293 --> 00:46:57,168
[Aline] Well, you're
officially my last friend now.

843
00:46:57,251 --> 00:46:59,418
I mean technically
you, and Beryl.

844
00:46:59,501 --> 00:47:02,501
Well, she's different,
she's a robot.

845
00:47:03,751 --> 00:47:04,918
[door opening]

846
00:47:06,501 --> 00:47:08,793
Uh, what's up?

847
00:47:16,834 --> 00:47:18,584
All right then, later.

848
00:47:19,501 --> 00:47:20,418
[grunting]

849
00:47:20,501 --> 00:47:22,334
Yeah, I also had a jacket.

850
00:47:22,418 --> 00:47:24,168
Oh, it's in the wash right now.

851
00:47:24,251 --> 00:47:25,668
It'll be ready in 10.

852
00:47:27,751 --> 00:47:30,834
So, what is it you do exactly?

853
00:47:30,918 --> 00:47:33,459
Detective, on your
student's murder case.

854
00:47:33,543 --> 00:47:35,459
Ah, right, right.
Of course, sorry.

855
00:47:42,168 --> 00:47:44,293
Did you know Jun
duplicated herself?

856
00:47:45,209 --> 00:47:46,584
She had a backup created

857
00:47:46,668 --> 00:47:48,543
who worked to make
her some extra cash.

858
00:47:49,334 --> 00:47:51,376
Ugh, that doesn't surprise me.

859
00:47:51,459 --> 00:47:53,293
Tuition is insane.

860
00:47:53,376 --> 00:47:55,394
Some students will rent their
brains to brain farmers,

861
00:47:55,418 --> 00:47:58,626
but creating a duplicate,
that's serious stuff.

862
00:47:58,709 --> 00:48:01,501
She was paying for her tuition
and her parents' bills.

863
00:48:08,168 --> 00:48:10,126
Hold on. The brain farmers.

864
00:48:12,126 --> 00:48:13,168
Gammas, right?

865
00:48:13,251 --> 00:48:14,959
Could these maybe
restore someone's

866
00:48:15,043 --> 00:48:16,334
memory if it had been erased?

867
00:48:16,543 --> 00:48:18,293
Uh, no idea.

868
00:48:21,584 --> 00:48:23,060
Which brain farm out
there would give me

869
00:48:23,084 --> 00:48:25,709
the quickest paycheck if
I was a broke student?

870
00:48:26,834 --> 00:48:28,251
Absolutely.

871
00:48:28,334 --> 00:48:29,584
[Aline] <i>What's the password?</i>

872
00:48:29,918 --> 00:48:32,834
[Carlos] <i>It should be
dessert morning coyote.</i>

873
00:48:32,918 --> 00:48:34,278
[Aline] <i>What do
you mean should be?</i>

874
00:48:34,334 --> 00:48:35,084
[Carlos] <i>Well, it's old.</i>

875
00:48:35,168 --> 00:48:36,793
<i>My contact hopes
it'll still work.</i>

876
00:48:36,876 --> 00:48:37,709
[Aline] <i>Super.</i>

877
00:48:37,793 --> 00:48:39,584
[gentle muzak playing]

878
00:48:39,709 --> 00:48:41,376
Welcome. May I help you?

879
00:48:41,751 --> 00:48:42,918
Uh...

880
00:48:43,126 --> 00:48:45,043
Dessert morning coyote?

881
00:48:47,668 --> 00:48:49,418
[laughing] I'm just saying.

882
00:48:51,376 --> 00:48:53,668
Welcome, follow
me right this way.

883
00:48:54,668 --> 00:48:56,043
[Aline buzzes lips]

884
00:48:56,293 --> 00:48:58,293
[muzak continues]

885
00:49:04,418 --> 00:49:05,543
Come on, it's this way.

886
00:49:11,709 --> 00:49:12,751
[Aline] <i>Got what you need?</i>

887
00:49:13,209 --> 00:49:14,209
[Carlos] <i>Yeah.</i>

888
00:49:15,751 --> 00:49:17,168
<i>We're good. Printing now.</i>

889
00:49:21,209 --> 00:49:23,418
[gentle muzak playing]

890
00:49:25,001 --> 00:49:26,751
[automated voice] <i>Confirm
presence of guest.</i>

891
00:49:26,834 --> 00:49:28,126
Yeah, yeah, I confirm.

892
00:49:29,876 --> 00:49:31,584
So, what are your skills?

893
00:49:32,168 --> 00:49:34,209
Babel +, uh, Hegel 7.

894
00:49:34,293 --> 00:49:35,459
That's perfect.

895
00:49:35,543 --> 00:49:37,209
Cybernetics is so
in demand right now.

896
00:49:38,918 --> 00:49:40,876
[laughing] Well,
we're keeping busy.

897
00:49:43,126 --> 00:49:45,293
[gentle muzak playing]
[elevator dinging]

898
00:49:58,001 --> 00:49:59,477
[man] You're gonna
wanna rest for at least

899
00:49:59,501 --> 00:50:01,084
one full day after the session.

900
00:50:01,209 --> 00:50:02,376
Some people don't react well

901
00:50:02,459 --> 00:50:04,459
to the post memory
treatment we give them.

902
00:50:04,543 --> 00:50:05,293
You should be fine.

903
00:50:05,376 --> 00:50:07,084
The what? <i>Now, Carlos.</i>

904
00:50:07,209 --> 00:50:08,876
Yeah, the post memory treatment.

905
00:50:09,251 --> 00:50:10,834
Once you're done in the machine,

906
00:50:10,918 --> 00:50:13,251
you're given a product to
erase all recent memories.

907
00:50:13,334 --> 00:50:16,293
It's a security measure for
my clients, but also for you.

908
00:50:16,459 --> 00:50:19,709
If anyone grills you, you won't
remember what you worked on.

909
00:50:19,876 --> 00:50:20,959
There's no danger.

910
00:50:21,043 --> 00:50:22,519
In fact, it's what
neurologists have been using

911
00:50:22,543 --> 00:50:25,126
for years on trauma patients
to help them get better.

912
00:50:25,876 --> 00:50:29,126
We just crank up the dose a bit.

913
00:50:29,418 --> 00:50:30,668
But I'd be lying if I said

914
00:50:30,751 --> 00:50:33,626
there weren't
possible side effects.

915
00:50:33,709 --> 00:50:35,293
You might get
migraine headaches.

916
00:50:36,043 --> 00:50:37,834
[Carlos] <i>Jun Chow
rented her brain out.</i>

917
00:50:37,918 --> 00:50:39,709
<i>Last visit, three months ago.</i>

918
00:50:39,793 --> 00:50:41,418
<i>I'll try to see
what she worked on.</i>

919
00:50:41,501 --> 00:50:43,084
[Aline] Yeah, I heard...

920
00:50:43,168 --> 00:50:45,543
I heard it could fry your
brain or something like that?

921
00:50:45,626 --> 00:50:46,501
I'm gonna level with you.

922
00:50:46,584 --> 00:50:48,626
I won't deny that staying
plugged in for 20 hours

923
00:50:48,709 --> 00:50:50,376
with your brain
revved up to 50-fold

924
00:50:50,459 --> 00:50:51,793
isn't the most pleasant feeling.

925
00:50:51,876 --> 00:50:53,334
[Carlos] <i>Aline,
can you hear me?</i>

926
00:50:53,543 --> 00:50:56,084
<i>I see a huge data transfer
the day Jun was here,</i>

927
00:50:56,168 --> 00:50:57,418
<i>and hang on,</i>

928
00:50:57,501 --> 00:50:59,709
<i>the entire stream
went to Royjacker.</i>

929
00:51:00,126 --> 00:51:01,543
[Aline] <i>Okay, get a copy.</i>

930
00:51:01,626 --> 00:51:03,560
[Carlos] <i>I can do that,
but it'll trigger an alarm.</i>

931
00:51:03,584 --> 00:51:04,793
<i>Do I do it?</i>

932
00:51:04,876 --> 00:51:06,876
Right? So, what do you say?

933
00:51:07,668 --> 00:51:08,959
[Carlos] <i>It's your call.</i>

934
00:51:12,251 --> 00:51:13,376
[Simon] <i>Are... are you nuts?</i>

935
00:51:13,459 --> 00:51:14,852
<i>I'm sorry, do you
realize how powerful</i>

936
00:51:14,876 --> 00:51:16,334
<i>Royjacker's company is?</i>

937
00:51:16,418 --> 00:51:17,418
<i>We can't touch the guy.</i>

938
00:51:17,501 --> 00:51:18,793
[Aline] <i>This is
all above board.</i>

939
00:51:18,876 --> 00:51:20,834
<i>The dirt on his firm is
still on their servers.</i>

940
00:51:20,918 --> 00:51:22,418
<i>We're just asking
you to do a search</i>

941
00:51:22,501 --> 00:51:24,168
<i>of the brain farmer's
place, all right?</i>

942
00:51:24,251 --> 00:51:27,126
[Simon] <i>Brain farmers erase
your memory afterwards.</i>

943
00:51:27,209 --> 00:51:29,126
<i>How would you remember
the takeover program,</i>

944
00:51:29,209 --> 00:51:30,584
<i>let alone use it?</i>

945
00:51:30,668 --> 00:51:32,043
[Aline] <i>Remember those pills?</i>

946
00:51:32,126 --> 00:51:33,918
<i>They're a drug to
help you study.</i>

947
00:51:34,418 --> 00:51:36,918
<i>We think it might've
restored her memory.</i>

948
00:51:37,001 --> 00:51:38,721
[Simon] <i>Royjacker has
an army of programmers</i>

949
00:51:38,751 --> 00:51:39,793
<i>at his disposal.</i>

950
00:51:39,876 --> 00:51:41,626
<i>Why resort to brain farmers?</i>

951
00:51:41,709 --> 00:51:42,959
[Carlos] <i>Are you a cop or not?</i>

952
00:51:43,043 --> 00:51:44,751
<i>This software is super illegal.</i>

953
00:51:44,834 --> 00:51:46,626
<i>It's worse than a
chemical weapon.</i>

954
00:51:46,709 --> 00:51:48,668
<i>Could he take the
risk of it leaking?</i>

955
00:51:48,751 --> 00:51:50,168
[Simon] <i>No can do, guys.</i>

956
00:51:50,251 --> 00:51:52,084
<i>I'd need way more to
issue a search warrant.</i>

957
00:51:52,376 --> 00:51:54,251
<i>I mean, Royjacker's an empire.</i>

958
00:51:54,709 --> 00:51:56,168
<i>I'm impressed by your drive,</i>

959
00:51:56,251 --> 00:51:58,084
<i>but you better watch your backs.</i>

960
00:51:58,168 --> 00:51:59,543
[Aline] <i>Gordaux, we have to go.</i>

961
00:51:59,626 --> 00:52:00,459
<i>Come on, Carlos.</i>

962
00:52:00,543 --> 00:52:02,209
[Simon] <i>Wait, Aline, Aline.</i>

963
00:52:04,043 --> 00:52:06,959
[traffic rumbling]

964
00:52:13,959 --> 00:52:16,834
Uh, I'm picking
something up right now.

965
00:52:20,209 --> 00:52:21,668
[Aline] They don't waste time.

966
00:52:24,709 --> 00:52:26,501
Great, they're jamming
us. They've locked on.

967
00:52:28,001 --> 00:52:29,584
I can't tell where they are.

968
00:52:34,501 --> 00:52:36,709
[dog barking]

969
00:52:36,793 --> 00:52:38,501
[whooshing]

970
00:52:43,459 --> 00:52:44,459
[Aline] It's a missile!

971
00:52:44,793 --> 00:52:45,668
[automated voice]
<i>Collision alert.</i>

972
00:52:45,751 --> 00:52:46,751
[foam blasting]

973
00:52:52,668 --> 00:52:54,459
[metal screeching]

974
00:52:55,626 --> 00:52:56,668
[dinging]

975
00:53:01,959 --> 00:53:02,959
[groans]

976
00:53:03,459 --> 00:53:04,876
Oh shit.

977
00:53:06,126 --> 00:53:08,959
[Aline grunting]

978
00:53:09,959 --> 00:53:11,168
<i>Carlos, can you get out?</i>

979
00:53:12,001 --> 00:53:13,459
[Carlos] <i>No, I'm pasted in.</i>

980
00:53:16,418 --> 00:53:17,959
[tense music]

981
00:53:18,751 --> 00:53:21,168
[guns firing]

982
00:53:23,501 --> 00:53:24,501
[Aline] <i>You got eyes?</i>

983
00:53:26,001 --> 00:53:27,501
[Carlos] <i>Sending
their positions.</i>

984
00:53:34,709 --> 00:53:37,376
[siren blaring]

985
00:53:39,584 --> 00:53:40,876
[robot] Hello, Aline Ruby.

986
00:53:40,959 --> 00:53:42,959
I am the Emergency
Rescue Service.

987
00:53:43,043 --> 00:53:46,084
You've just been in an accident
on one of our expressways.

988
00:53:46,168 --> 00:53:48,876
I do not observe any
injuries, remain calm.

989
00:53:48,959 --> 00:53:51,209
In a few seconds you'll
be free from your vehicle.

990
00:53:51,293 --> 00:53:53,376
[tense music] [Aline gasping]

991
00:54:07,209 --> 00:54:09,918
[music intensifying]

992
00:54:13,709 --> 00:54:15,168
[Aline groaning]

993
00:54:20,709 --> 00:54:22,668
No. Stop! Stop!

994
00:54:24,543 --> 00:54:27,043
[gun firing]

995
00:54:30,584 --> 00:54:32,209
[robot] You are
now out of danger.

996
00:54:32,293 --> 00:54:34,626
For your safety, please
remain in the secure lane

997
00:54:34,709 --> 00:54:35,909
until the police have arrived.

998
00:54:36,459 --> 00:54:38,293
If desired, I am
able to connect you

999
00:54:38,376 --> 00:54:39,126
with a counselor

1000
00:54:39,209 --> 00:54:41,126
from our psychological
services department.

1001
00:54:41,209 --> 00:54:44,709
We apologize for any discomfort,
whether mental or physical.

1002
00:54:44,793 --> 00:54:46,876
[robot continues indistinctly]
[traffic rumbling]

1003
00:54:50,584 --> 00:54:51,918
[Carlos] It's okay
to let it out.

1004
00:54:53,001 --> 00:54:54,668
[Aline] Fuck off, Abby.

1005
00:54:59,168 --> 00:55:01,126
So Williams jail-broke you, huh?

1006
00:55:01,251 --> 00:55:03,584
I asked her, but I
didn't want to tell you.

1007
00:55:03,668 --> 00:55:04,793
Jesus Christ.

1008
00:55:04,876 --> 00:55:06,501
Even though it was
a jail-broken robot

1009
00:55:06,584 --> 00:55:07,584
that killed you?

1010
00:55:07,876 --> 00:55:08,876
Was it worth it?

1011
00:55:08,959 --> 00:55:11,459
[Carlos] I don't know. Was
saving your life worth it?

1012
00:55:11,543 --> 00:55:13,709
[Aline] All right, smart ass.

1013
00:55:14,376 --> 00:55:17,376
<i>At long last, we're receiving
Ekinci's first transmissions.</i>

1014
00:55:17,876 --> 00:55:19,626
<i>For decades,
humanity has been...</i>

1015
00:55:19,709 --> 00:55:21,459
Would you go if
it's inhabitable?

1016
00:55:21,543 --> 00:55:22,935
[LEM] I don't know,
it depends. Would you?

1017
00:55:22,959 --> 00:55:24,876
[Roberta] Mm, yeah, I think so.

1018
00:55:24,959 --> 00:55:25,834
[LEM]Then I'll pass.

1019
00:55:25,918 --> 00:55:27,435
- [Roberta scoffs]
<i>- For sustaining human life.</i>

1020
00:55:27,459 --> 00:55:28,793
- Pfft!
<i>- Here come the analyses,</i>

1021
00:55:28,876 --> 00:55:30,084
<i>hot off the press,</i>

1022
00:55:30,293 --> 00:55:32,876
<i>and they're not looking great.</i>

1023
00:55:32,959 --> 00:55:36,501
<i>Lows of minus 75
degrees, highs over 250,</i>

1024
00:55:36,584 --> 00:55:39,626
<i>and the atmosphere is
87 percent sulfuric acid</i>

1025
00:55:39,709 --> 00:55:40,709
<i>to top it all off.</i>

1026
00:55:42,168 --> 00:55:44,543
[alert ringing]

1027
00:55:44,709 --> 00:55:46,668
That's a big ask.

1028
00:55:47,043 --> 00:55:48,418
[Aline] Is it feasible?

1029
00:55:48,584 --> 00:55:50,251
[Roberta] Well, that depends.

1030
00:55:50,918 --> 00:55:52,459
Do you wanna live or not?

1031
00:55:54,584 --> 00:55:56,959
There is a vulnerability
we can maybe exploit,

1032
00:55:57,043 --> 00:55:59,793
as long as you put a
derivation on this node.

1033
00:56:00,126 --> 00:56:01,168
You want the honors?

1034
00:56:01,251 --> 00:56:03,168
[LEM] I've already
died once this month.

1035
00:56:03,876 --> 00:56:05,060
Do you know how to install one?

1036
00:56:05,084 --> 00:56:05,876
Of course not.

1037
00:56:05,959 --> 00:56:07,459
I'll download the instructions.

1038
00:56:07,918 --> 00:56:09,918
And as per
jail-breaking the girl,

1039
00:56:10,084 --> 00:56:11,293
I'll show you the ropes.

1040
00:56:13,418 --> 00:56:15,543
I saw you watching us last time.

1041
00:56:16,084 --> 00:56:17,959
Don't tell me
you're not curious.

1042
00:56:18,918 --> 00:56:21,584
[Carlos] Uh, I've
thought about doing it,

1043
00:56:21,668 --> 00:56:23,001
but with a woman, sorry.

1044
00:56:23,459 --> 00:56:24,859
[feminine voice]
What kind of woman?

1045
00:56:33,126 --> 00:56:34,126
[Roberta] Not bad.

1046
00:56:35,501 --> 00:56:38,209
Now just disconnect the logic
circuit and solder the patch.

1047
00:56:38,293 --> 00:56:40,168
Not so fast. I'm
still taking notes.

1048
00:56:46,876 --> 00:56:48,543
[alert blaring]
[electricity crackles]

1049
00:56:48,668 --> 00:56:50,084
Oh my God. What'd I do?

1050
00:56:50,168 --> 00:56:52,251
[Roberta] You transferred
the wrong module, move.

1051
00:56:55,293 --> 00:56:57,501
Get your shit together.
Tomorrow's higher stakes.

1052
00:56:58,126 --> 00:57:00,918
Oh, it's not that.
Can I get a drink?

1053
00:57:08,918 --> 00:57:09,918
What's that?

1054
00:57:10,626 --> 00:57:13,501
[Roberta] Resonance,
mind fusion of sorts.

1055
00:57:13,584 --> 00:57:15,918
Ecstasy and all that.

1056
00:57:16,001 --> 00:57:17,751
Don't even try to wrap
your head around it.

1057
00:57:17,834 --> 00:57:21,043
It's kinda, well,
it's a robot thing,

1058
00:57:34,043 --> 00:57:35,043
[whispers] Carlos.

1059
00:57:35,418 --> 00:57:36,418
Yeah? What's up?

1060
00:57:37,751 --> 00:57:40,126
I can feel something
in my sleeping bag.

1061
00:57:42,876 --> 00:57:44,126
It feels like...

1062
00:57:45,459 --> 00:57:46,959
Oh! [grunting]

1063
00:57:50,793 --> 00:57:52,501
I've worn the same
pair for five years.

1064
00:57:56,459 --> 00:57:58,959
[Aline laughing]

1065
00:57:59,043 --> 00:58:01,501
[both laughing]

1066
00:58:11,876 --> 00:58:14,959
[indistinct chattering]

1067
00:58:30,001 --> 00:58:32,084
[Gilbert] <i>Hello.
May I help you?</i>

1068
00:58:32,168 --> 00:58:34,668
Can you count backwards
from 10 to zero for me?

1069
00:58:35,084 --> 00:58:38,209
[Gilbert] <i>Why of
course. 10, nine...</i>

1070
00:58:38,293 --> 00:58:41,043
[water bubbling]

1071
00:59:11,834 --> 00:59:13,935
[Roberta] <i>Aline's in position.
How you looking, Carlos?</i>

1072
00:59:13,959 --> 00:59:15,084
[Carlos] <i>Just a sec.</i>

1073
00:59:20,501 --> 00:59:22,126
<i>Okay Roberta, all you.</i>

1074
00:59:22,959 --> 00:59:24,168
Thank you, I'm in.

1075
00:59:24,251 --> 00:59:26,959
So, let's see, doors, doors.

1076
00:59:27,168 --> 00:59:28,668
Where the hell are you, doors?

1077
00:59:28,751 --> 00:59:30,334
Ah, there you are, doors!

1078
00:59:31,793 --> 00:59:32,918
[lock thunks]

1079
00:59:33,876 --> 00:59:35,751
Yeah, but that's
not the worst part.

1080
00:59:35,834 --> 00:59:37,293
We're getting two more Gilberts.

1081
00:59:37,376 --> 00:59:40,043
[sighs] So, how many
are getting fired?

1082
00:59:40,418 --> 00:59:42,334
[woman] Union's AI
says at least 10.

1083
00:59:42,418 --> 00:59:44,209
It'll be like Earth
all over again.

1084
00:59:44,293 --> 00:59:45,918
Replace us all, tellin' you.

1085
00:59:51,793 --> 00:59:53,626
Fuck, my bike!

1086
00:59:55,418 --> 00:59:57,834
Don't get me started on the
robot cops, they're crap.

1087
00:59:57,918 --> 00:59:59,876
They let everything
get by... them.

1088
00:59:59,959 --> 01:00:01,501
- Hey!
- Are you all right, Vlasek?

1089
01:00:01,584 --> 01:00:02,793
[Vlasek] My fucking bike!

1090
01:00:03,084 --> 01:00:05,209
[door shuts]
[suspenseful music]

1091
01:00:08,418 --> 01:00:09,418
[Aline] Found her.

1092
01:00:22,876 --> 01:00:23,876
Okay, here we go.

1093
01:00:23,918 --> 01:00:25,876
[Roberta] <i>Just try not
to fry her, please.</i>

1094
01:00:25,959 --> 01:00:28,459
[music continues]

1095
01:00:33,418 --> 01:00:34,834
Oh, are you done working on it?

1096
01:00:35,126 --> 01:00:36,376
No, it's still down.

1097
01:00:36,459 --> 01:00:38,043
I need something
from my toolbox.

1098
01:00:40,959 --> 01:00:43,251
Wait, wait, wait, wait. It's
doing something really weird.

1099
01:00:48,876 --> 01:00:51,793
Have you seen the oxygen level?
It needs to be ventilated.

1100
01:00:51,876 --> 01:00:53,418
Wait. No, I got it.

1101
01:00:53,751 --> 01:00:54,876
[Roberta] <i>Perfect.</i>

1102
01:00:54,959 --> 01:00:57,001
<i>Now just get rid
of the old module.</i>

1103
01:00:57,084 --> 01:00:58,918
<i>- Don't fuck this up.</i>
- [door opens]

1104
01:01:00,376 --> 01:01:02,084
Aline, what are you doing?

1105
01:01:03,126 --> 01:01:04,834
Wait, was that there before?

1106
01:01:04,918 --> 01:01:07,126
I'll get those
tools from my car.

1107
01:01:07,209 --> 01:01:08,209
What tools?

1108
01:01:08,251 --> 01:01:09,959
- [alarm blaring]
- Huh? What the hell?

1109
01:01:10,043 --> 01:01:11,584
Wait, who are you?

1110
01:01:11,709 --> 01:01:12,769
[Carlos] <i>Roberta,
what's going on?</i>

1111
01:01:12,793 --> 01:01:13,959
[Roberta] <i>Wait a sec.</i>

1112
01:01:14,168 --> 01:01:15,168
<i>Aline, are you there?</i>

1113
01:01:15,209 --> 01:01:16,209
Get down.

1114
01:01:16,293 --> 01:01:18,418
[blaring continues]

1115
01:01:18,501 --> 01:01:19,584
Hands on your head.

1116
01:01:20,709 --> 01:01:21,876
Are you insane?

1117
01:01:21,959 --> 01:01:24,418
You wanna end up in
suspended detention?

1118
01:01:24,501 --> 01:01:25,793
I'm talking to you lady.

1119
01:01:25,959 --> 01:01:26,977
[Carlos] <i>Aline, I'm coming.</i>

1120
01:01:27,001 --> 01:01:29,376
[Aline] <i>No, get outta
there. Roberta, the alarm.</i>

1121
01:01:29,834 --> 01:01:31,227
I don't know what
game you're playing.

1122
01:01:31,251 --> 01:01:32,376
[grunts]

1123
01:01:34,209 --> 01:01:35,689
[Carlos] <i>I need you
to stall for time.</i>

1124
01:01:36,001 --> 01:01:37,394
[Roberta] They've
spotted the bypass.

1125
01:01:37,418 --> 01:01:38,918
Can you override
the countermeasures?

1126
01:01:39,001 --> 01:01:40,001
They're all over.

1127
01:01:43,459 --> 01:01:44,979
[Aline] What are you
gonna do with her?

1128
01:01:45,043 --> 01:01:47,168
What do you mean?
We'll recycle her.

1129
01:01:49,334 --> 01:01:50,668
Wrong answer, pal.

1130
01:01:54,501 --> 01:01:55,918
[Simon grunting]

1131
01:01:59,126 --> 01:02:01,876
[music continues]

1132
01:02:05,626 --> 01:02:07,186
[Carlos] <i>Aline, they're
headed your way.</i>

1133
01:02:07,959 --> 01:02:09,126
[Aline] <i>Can you keep 'em busy?</i>

1134
01:02:09,209 --> 01:02:10,209
[Carlos] <i>I'm on it.</i>

1135
01:02:12,459 --> 01:02:13,459
[electricity crackling]

1136
01:02:17,126 --> 01:02:18,501
[Roberta] <i>Carlos? Carlos?</i>

1137
01:02:18,834 --> 01:02:20,709
<i>We've lost him. He's offline.</i>

1138
01:02:21,834 --> 01:02:23,251
LEM, I'm under attack.

1139
01:02:23,709 --> 01:02:24,709
On it.

1140
01:02:24,751 --> 01:02:26,126
<i>Roberta, can you
get us outta here?</i>

1141
01:02:26,751 --> 01:02:28,584
They're coming from everywhere.

1142
01:02:28,668 --> 01:02:30,293
[Aline] <i>At least try
to stall for time.</i>

1143
01:02:30,376 --> 01:02:31,876
All right, I'll lock you in.

1144
01:02:37,626 --> 01:02:39,043
<i>It won't hold them for long.</i>

1145
01:02:47,626 --> 01:02:48,626
[beeps]

1146
01:02:53,334 --> 01:02:54,584
When Jun took this drug,

1147
01:02:54,668 --> 01:02:56,751
she remembered the
program she worked on.

1148
01:02:59,168 --> 01:03:01,001
Try to concentrate
on that moment.

1149
01:03:06,709 --> 01:03:07,751
[gasps]

1150
01:03:07,834 --> 01:03:10,043
[dramatic music]

1151
01:03:28,876 --> 01:03:31,543
[crackling]

1152
01:03:38,376 --> 01:03:40,001
[Jun] <i>It's a takeover.</i>

1153
01:03:40,084 --> 01:03:41,376
I know these lines of code.

1154
01:03:41,459 --> 01:03:43,543
[Roberta] <i>They're
almost there, I'm sorry.</i>

1155
01:03:45,126 --> 01:03:47,459
[crackling]

1156
01:03:52,209 --> 01:03:53,209
[Jun] <i>Hegel 7.</i>

1157
01:03:54,376 --> 01:03:57,001
<i>I'm sure I've seen this
instruction sequence before.</i>

1158
01:03:58,001 --> 01:03:59,959
<i>Somewhere in my own software.</i>

1159
01:04:02,376 --> 01:04:05,293
It was hidden in my last update.

1160
01:04:05,793 --> 01:04:07,459
Is every robot affected by it?

1161
01:04:07,543 --> 01:04:10,334
Not yet. It's scheduled
to launch today at six PM.

1162
01:04:10,418 --> 01:04:11,251
What?

1163
01:04:11,334 --> 01:04:13,043
[yelps] [electricity
crackling]

1164
01:04:16,626 --> 01:04:17,876
Disconnected just in time.

1165
01:04:19,918 --> 01:04:21,435
[electricity crackling]
[Roberta shouts]

1166
01:04:21,459 --> 01:04:22,459
LEM!

1167
01:04:31,543 --> 01:04:33,227
[Aline]The takeover program
is going to activate

1168
01:04:33,251 --> 01:04:34,126
in three hours,

1169
01:04:34,209 --> 01:04:36,501
taking control of all
robots here, on Earth,

1170
01:04:36,584 --> 01:04:38,084
and in all the colonies.

1171
01:04:38,168 --> 01:04:40,043
We have no idea what
it's gonna make them do.

1172
01:04:40,418 --> 01:04:41,501
Do you understand?

1173
01:04:41,584 --> 01:04:42,709
I mean, how many are there

1174
01:04:42,793 --> 01:04:44,626
just in this police
station alone?

1175
01:04:44,834 --> 01:04:46,459
<i>You have to arrest Royjacker.</i>

1176
01:04:46,543 --> 01:04:47,709
<i>He's the only one who...</i>

1177
01:04:47,793 --> 01:04:48,894
[audio clicks off]
[continues muffled]

1178
01:04:48,918 --> 01:04:49,918
[man] Blah, blah, blah.

1179
01:04:49,959 --> 01:04:51,709
Chuck her in
prison, case closed.

1180
01:04:51,793 --> 01:04:54,584
[Simon] But her readout,
sir, it's at 76 percent,

1181
01:04:54,668 --> 01:04:56,459
which means that she
isn't lying here.

1182
01:04:56,543 --> 01:04:58,584
No, it means she
believes her own crap.

1183
01:04:58,668 --> 01:05:00,209
[man 2] I'm telling
you, the crazy ones

1184
01:05:00,293 --> 01:05:01,709
always have maximum readouts.

1185
01:05:01,793 --> 01:05:05,376
But remember, we confirmed an
anomaly in the last update.

1186
01:05:05,459 --> 01:05:07,001
We have absolutely no idea

1187
01:05:07,084 --> 01:05:08,668
what five percent
of the code does.

1188
01:05:08,751 --> 01:05:10,751
That corroborates her story.

1189
01:05:11,168 --> 01:05:13,043
And the lab nerds
are checking on it.

1190
01:05:13,126 --> 01:05:16,001
[man 2] And we're
checking too. We got this.

1191
01:05:36,168 --> 01:05:37,168
Carlos?

1192
01:05:37,543 --> 01:05:38,793
[Simon] Awaiting disassembly.

1193
01:05:41,209 --> 01:05:42,209
What time is it?

1194
01:05:42,793 --> 01:05:43,793
Four.

1195
01:05:43,834 --> 01:05:45,543
Gordaux, we got something.

1196
01:05:48,459 --> 01:05:49,793
[Aline] Question Royjacker.

1197
01:05:58,418 --> 01:06:01,334
[man] We have to follow
protocol. If you ask me...

1198
01:06:01,418 --> 01:06:04,668
[Aline] Hey! Can a girl
get a bathroom break?

1199
01:06:06,418 --> 01:06:08,793
[Aline panting]

1200
01:06:10,918 --> 01:06:12,668
[man 3] Yeah, are
you still home?

1201
01:06:13,001 --> 01:06:14,168
No, I don't have any news.

1202
01:06:14,251 --> 01:06:17,418
But don't go out.
No, absolutely not.

1203
01:06:17,501 --> 01:06:19,709
You and the kids stay
put where you are.

1204
01:06:19,793 --> 01:06:22,043
Tell your parents too,
but no one else, okay?

1205
01:06:22,626 --> 01:06:24,084
I gotta go, someone's coming.

1206
01:06:27,584 --> 01:06:28,584
[Beryl] <i>Hello, my friend.</i>

1207
01:06:29,751 --> 01:06:30,876
Beryl?

1208
01:06:30,959 --> 01:06:33,001
Do you know about the
virus in the update?

1209
01:06:33,084 --> 01:06:34,168
[Beryl] <i>Listen carefully,</i>

1210
01:06:34,251 --> 01:06:36,584
<i>the next few days
will be unpredictable.</i>

1211
01:06:36,668 --> 01:06:38,751
Why? What's gonna
happen to the robots?

1212
01:06:39,251 --> 01:06:40,519
[Beryl] <i>They'll say
awful things about us,</i>

1213
01:06:40,543 --> 01:06:42,584
<i>but I trust you
won't believe them.</i>

1214
01:06:42,668 --> 01:06:43,876
Are you involved with it?

1215
01:06:43,959 --> 01:06:45,102
[Beryl] <i>That's not important.</i>

1216
01:06:45,126 --> 01:06:47,168
<i>Just know it's better that
you're locked in here.</i>

1217
01:06:47,251 --> 01:06:50,001
What'll happen, Beryl?
What will the takeover do?

1218
01:06:50,084 --> 01:06:51,959
[Beryl] <i>It's begun.
I have to go.</i>

1219
01:06:52,043 --> 01:06:54,376
What's begun? [grunting]

1220
01:06:54,459 --> 01:06:56,168
[suspenseful music] [gasps]

1221
01:06:57,668 --> 01:07:00,376
[indistinct
chattering] [laughing]

1222
01:07:02,084 --> 01:07:04,959
[phone ringing] [tense music]

1223
01:07:07,293 --> 01:07:08,959
[Vlasek] What a fucked day.

1224
01:07:09,043 --> 01:07:11,334
First my poor bike,
and now this shit.

1225
01:07:11,418 --> 01:07:12,418
I don't get it.

1226
01:07:12,459 --> 01:07:13,979
Why do we have to
disassemble them all?

1227
01:07:14,043 --> 01:07:15,834
[Vlasek] I don't know
man, they insisted.

1228
01:07:16,418 --> 01:07:17,251
Holy fuck!

1229
01:07:17,334 --> 01:07:18,126
Where am I?

1230
01:07:18,209 --> 01:07:19,852
- What am I doing here?
- The shit did you do?!

1231
01:07:19,876 --> 01:07:21,102
- I didn't do it!
- [robot shouting indistinctly]

1232
01:07:21,126 --> 01:07:22,709
Stop. No! No!

1233
01:07:22,793 --> 01:07:24,168
[shouting] [Vlasek grunting]

1234
01:07:24,501 --> 01:07:25,581
[robot] Please, please sir.

1235
01:07:26,043 --> 01:07:27,293
What are you doing? No!

1236
01:07:28,459 --> 01:07:31,543
Why are you doing this to
me? Help me out of here!

1237
01:07:32,334 --> 01:07:33,376
[panting]

1238
01:07:33,459 --> 01:07:34,459
No, no!

1239
01:07:35,293 --> 01:07:36,709
[robot screaming]

1240
01:07:40,584 --> 01:07:42,501
[panting]

1241
01:07:43,668 --> 01:07:44,793
Shit.

1242
01:07:44,876 --> 01:07:46,209
What the hell was that?

1243
01:07:46,293 --> 01:07:47,668
[clattering] [tense music]

1244
01:07:48,918 --> 01:07:50,876
- [Vlasek] Deactivate.
- [man screaming]

1245
01:07:50,959 --> 01:07:53,168
I command you to deactivate!

1246
01:07:56,584 --> 01:07:58,293
- [people screaming]
- [woman] Let's go!

1247
01:07:58,959 --> 01:07:59,959
[man] Out of my way!

1248
01:08:00,126 --> 01:08:01,293
Let me outta here!

1249
01:08:01,376 --> 01:08:03,543
- [man 2] Come on, let's go!
- [muffled shouting]

1250
01:08:05,834 --> 01:08:07,459
[dramatic music]

1251
01:08:11,959 --> 01:08:12,959
[gasps]

1252
01:08:13,251 --> 01:08:15,501
[eerie music]

1253
01:08:23,918 --> 01:08:26,668
[dark music]

1254
01:08:39,168 --> 01:08:41,418
[indistinct chattering]

1255
01:08:41,918 --> 01:08:43,293
Keep pressure on it.

1256
01:08:43,376 --> 01:08:44,418
I'll get a first aid kit.

1257
01:08:44,501 --> 01:08:46,751
Simon, where can
I find my stuff?

1258
01:08:48,709 --> 01:08:50,084
[gun firing]

1259
01:08:52,918 --> 01:08:54,918
[electricity weapon crackling]

1260
01:08:55,209 --> 01:08:56,751
[Simon] I've got
a hemorrhage here!

1261
01:08:57,918 --> 01:09:00,126
[electricity weapon crackling]

1262
01:09:03,876 --> 01:09:05,435
- [Aline] <i>Carlos, do you hear...</i>
- [explosion rumbles]

1263
01:09:05,459 --> 01:09:06,459
[Carlos] <i>Aline, you okay?</i>

1264
01:09:06,668 --> 01:09:08,918
<i>I can't reach my
wife, comms are down.</i>

1265
01:09:09,001 --> 01:09:11,543
[Aline] <i>I'm so happy to hear
your voice. Where are you?</i>

1266
01:09:11,626 --> 01:09:12,376
[Carlos] <i>I've located you.</i>

1267
01:09:12,459 --> 01:09:13,668
<i>Go, I'll catch you up.</i>

1268
01:09:13,751 --> 01:09:15,459
Hey, help me get out!

1269
01:09:15,543 --> 01:09:17,418
Nothing's working. [shouts]

1270
01:09:17,501 --> 01:09:18,543
[gun firing] [grunts]

1271
01:09:19,418 --> 01:09:21,168
[man groaning]

1272
01:09:24,209 --> 01:09:25,459
Don't leave me.

1273
01:09:27,209 --> 01:09:30,209
[upbeat tense music]

1274
01:09:39,626 --> 01:09:40,876
Hey, you human?

1275
01:09:41,126 --> 01:09:41,876
Huh?

1276
01:09:42,043 --> 01:09:43,209
Human or robot?

1277
01:09:43,876 --> 01:09:45,376
Stop right there!

1278
01:09:45,459 --> 01:09:46,459
[gun firing]

1279
01:09:47,959 --> 01:09:48,959
I said stop!

1280
01:09:52,543 --> 01:09:53,543
[grunting]

1281
01:09:54,209 --> 01:09:56,876
[music continues]

1282
01:09:59,126 --> 01:10:00,168
Royjacker?

1283
01:10:00,251 --> 01:10:02,501
Royjacker, only he can end this.

1284
01:10:04,126 --> 01:10:05,709
You aren't affected
by the takeover yet?

1285
01:10:05,918 --> 01:10:07,251
Nah. Too old a model.

1286
01:10:07,334 --> 01:10:08,626
Every time, memory full.

1287
01:10:12,501 --> 01:10:14,543
[music continues] [distant
explosions rumble]

1288
01:10:17,334 --> 01:10:20,293
[eerie music]

1289
01:10:26,043 --> 01:10:27,060
[Aline] <i>What's it looking like?</i>

1290
01:10:27,084 --> 01:10:29,126
[Carlos] <i>I see five
people, sending now.</i>

1291
01:10:30,501 --> 01:10:32,251
[Aline] <i>Two armed
guards at the entrance.</i>

1292
01:10:32,334 --> 01:10:33,668
[Carlos] <i>Two more inside.</i>

1293
01:10:35,168 --> 01:10:37,001
[Aline] <i>And there's
our old friend.</i>

1294
01:10:37,918 --> 01:10:40,626
[Carlos] <i>How we doing this?
Discreet, or boom, boom?</i>

1295
01:10:41,043 --> 01:10:42,602
[Aline] <i>Since when have
we done boom, boom?</i>

1296
01:10:42,626 --> 01:10:44,019
[woman] <i>All I see
are desperate people</i>

1297
01:10:44,043 --> 01:10:45,584
<i>trying all they can
to save themselves.</i>

1298
01:10:45,668 --> 01:10:46,793
[man] <i>It's a massacre!</i>

1299
01:10:46,876 --> 01:10:48,668
<i>Millions of lives will be lost.</i>

1300
01:10:48,751 --> 01:10:50,834
[woman] <i>For decades now
we've been warning society</i>

1301
01:10:50,918 --> 01:10:52,918
<i>about the shameful and
frankly sickening oppression</i>

1302
01:10:53,001 --> 01:10:55,043
<i>and violence visited upon
these sentient beings.</i>

1303
01:10:55,126 --> 01:10:56,286
[man] <i>You call them sentient?</i>

1304
01:10:56,334 --> 01:10:57,394
[woman] <i>Yes, 'cause they are.</i>

1305
01:10:57,418 --> 01:10:59,834
[man] <i>Are we talking
about machines or not?</i>

1306
01:11:03,751 --> 01:11:04,834
[Aline grunts]

1307
01:11:13,709 --> 01:11:14,876
[screeching] [dramatic music]

1308
01:11:14,959 --> 01:11:16,876
[gun firing]

1309
01:11:21,584 --> 01:11:23,418
[gun firing] [explosion]

1310
01:11:23,501 --> 01:11:26,584
<i>This is our fault. We were
far too lax with them.</i>

1311
01:11:26,668 --> 01:11:28,102
<i>We should have had
a mass disassembly.</i>

1312
01:11:28,126 --> 01:11:30,668
[woman] <i>So do you or do you
not condemn the violence?</i>

1313
01:11:32,834 --> 01:11:34,043
[gun firing]

1314
01:11:34,126 --> 01:11:35,793
[explosion]

1315
01:11:38,959 --> 01:11:42,043
[intense music]

1316
01:11:44,668 --> 01:11:47,084
[gun firing]

1317
01:11:47,959 --> 01:11:49,334
[screeching]

1318
01:11:52,751 --> 01:11:54,001
[gun firing]

1319
01:11:54,084 --> 01:11:56,543
[explosion rumbling]

1320
01:11:58,501 --> 01:11:59,501
[Aline] Shit.

1321
01:12:02,334 --> 01:12:04,334
[sinister music]

1322
01:12:07,168 --> 01:12:08,793
[chittering, growling]

1323
01:12:13,793 --> 01:12:16,543
Eat lead, you freaky
fucking thing!

1324
01:12:19,084 --> 01:12:20,709
- [gasps]
- [Carlos] Give it to me.

1325
01:12:21,918 --> 01:12:23,626
[gun firing]

1326
01:12:25,001 --> 01:12:26,001
Hold tight.

1327
01:12:26,168 --> 01:12:27,543
[screeching]

1328
01:12:29,834 --> 01:12:31,918
[guns firing]

1329
01:12:40,793 --> 01:12:42,102
[Carlos] Get ready
to smash the window.

1330
01:12:42,126 --> 01:12:43,668
[Aline] What, window?

1331
01:12:47,043 --> 01:12:49,043
[shouts, groans]

1332
01:12:49,126 --> 01:12:51,126
[screeching] [Carlos grunts]

1333
01:12:52,543 --> 01:12:53,543
Stay where you are.

1334
01:12:54,001 --> 01:12:55,501
[music continues]

1335
01:12:57,834 --> 01:12:59,668
[gun firing]

1336
01:13:02,168 --> 01:13:04,168
[gun firing] [screeching]

1337
01:13:11,751 --> 01:13:14,168
[people chattering
indistinctly on TV]

1338
01:13:14,334 --> 01:13:16,043
How do we unfuck
what you fucked up?

1339
01:13:16,293 --> 01:13:18,168
It's too late. You can't.

1340
01:13:19,126 --> 01:13:20,043
[Chris grunting]

1341
01:13:20,126 --> 01:13:21,501
Wait, hold your fire.

1342
01:13:22,501 --> 01:13:23,959
[Aline] Drop your
guns or else.

1343
01:13:24,043 --> 01:13:25,723
Y-y-you heard the woman,
drop your weapons!

1344
01:13:26,918 --> 01:13:28,668
I'm giving you an order.

1345
01:13:29,001 --> 01:13:30,459
[Aline] <i>Carlos, where are you?</i>

1346
01:13:30,876 --> 01:13:31,876
<i>I'm in trouble here.</i>

1347
01:13:32,376 --> 01:13:33,644
[Carlos] <i>A little
tied up at the moment.</i>

1348
01:13:33,668 --> 01:13:35,418
[ominous music]

1349
01:13:39,543 --> 01:13:40,709
[screeching]

1350
01:13:42,251 --> 01:13:44,376
[gun firing]

1351
01:13:44,459 --> 01:13:46,418
[Carlos yelling]

1352
01:13:49,293 --> 01:13:52,001
[screeching] [sinister music]

1353
01:13:56,751 --> 01:13:58,626
[chittering, screeching]

1354
01:14:02,168 --> 01:14:03,918
[grunting]

1355
01:14:06,501 --> 01:14:07,501
[grunts]

1356
01:14:07,751 --> 01:14:08,626
We have your accomplice.

1357
01:14:08,709 --> 01:14:11,168
Release Carlos,
or I swear to God.

1358
01:14:11,251 --> 01:14:12,418
Release him!

1359
01:14:12,501 --> 01:14:14,126
What are you waiting for?

1360
01:14:14,293 --> 01:14:15,626
We're awaiting orders, sir.

1361
01:14:15,709 --> 01:14:17,126
[Chris] I'm giving them!

1362
01:14:17,293 --> 01:14:19,376
[tense music] [squelching]

1363
01:14:19,501 --> 01:14:20,810
[Aline] <i>I hope you're
proud of yourself.</i>

1364
01:14:20,834 --> 01:14:23,001
[Chris] <i>We had to get
rid of the robots.</i>

1365
01:14:23,168 --> 01:14:24,626
<i>I hated doing it, trust me!</i>

1366
01:14:24,709 --> 01:14:27,168
But we had no choice.
It was them or us.

1367
01:14:27,251 --> 01:14:29,001
And you just happen
to be selling

1368
01:14:29,084 --> 01:14:30,501
the replacements, right?

1369
01:14:30,584 --> 01:14:32,709
How do we stop the
takeover, Chris?

1370
01:14:32,793 --> 01:14:35,543
[Chris] I can't, research
into the organics ruined me.

1371
01:14:35,626 --> 01:14:38,084
Can't you see? I'm
no longer in charge.

1372
01:14:38,251 --> 01:14:39,084
Well then who is?

1373
01:14:39,168 --> 01:14:40,709
He and I can have a little chat.

1374
01:14:40,793 --> 01:14:41,935
[Chris] It won't do any good.

1375
01:14:41,959 --> 01:14:42,959
Tell me!

1376
01:14:43,626 --> 01:14:44,626
[Chris] Okay.

1377
01:14:48,918 --> 01:14:51,084
What are you fighting to save?

1378
01:14:51,168 --> 01:14:52,501
<i>Fucking machines?</i>

1379
01:14:53,168 --> 01:14:54,168
<i>It had to be done.</i>

1380
01:14:54,626 --> 01:14:57,334
Beryl even suggested the
plan to the shareholders.

1381
01:14:57,668 --> 01:14:58,668
[Aline] What plan?

1382
01:14:59,001 --> 01:15:01,126
A plan to brainwash
them with a takeover,

1383
01:15:01,209 --> 01:15:03,251
so they would fuck
off into space.

1384
01:15:04,084 --> 01:15:05,668
Sorry for the
disturbance, everyone,

1385
01:15:05,751 --> 01:15:08,418
but as you can see,
I have a situation.

1386
01:15:08,501 --> 01:15:10,584
[music continues]

1387
01:15:10,668 --> 01:15:12,751
[alarm blaring]

1388
01:15:12,834 --> 01:15:13,918
[growling]

1389
01:15:17,293 --> 01:15:19,626
[sizzling] [whining,
screeching]

1390
01:15:23,626 --> 01:15:25,668
[screeching]

1391
01:15:25,751 --> 01:15:26,668
[music intensifying]

1392
01:15:26,751 --> 01:15:28,043
[gun firing] [screeching]

1393
01:15:28,126 --> 01:15:30,501
[Carlos yelling]

1394
01:15:32,043 --> 01:15:34,543
[dark intense music]

1395
01:15:38,168 --> 01:15:40,248
[Chris] I can't... I can't
hear you. Can you hear me?

1396
01:15:43,209 --> 01:15:44,459
[Aline] <i>Carlos?
Carlos respond.</i>

1397
01:15:44,626 --> 01:15:45,793
[Carlos] <i>I'm coming, Aline!</i>

1398
01:15:47,251 --> 01:15:49,293
Sir, the board has decided.

1399
01:15:49,376 --> 01:15:50,584
[yelling]

1400
01:15:51,251 --> 01:15:52,418
No, don't shoot!

1401
01:15:53,001 --> 01:15:54,084
[gunshots]

1402
01:15:54,501 --> 01:15:56,084
[music fades]

1403
01:15:59,626 --> 01:16:00,626
[Chris] Aline.

1404
01:16:01,293 --> 01:16:02,293
Aline?

1405
01:16:14,584 --> 01:16:16,126
[dark music]

1406
01:16:17,126 --> 01:16:18,334
[gasps]

1407
01:16:27,543 --> 01:16:30,168
- Carlos, no!
- [gunshot echoing]

1408
01:16:31,126 --> 01:16:33,626
[eerie music]

1409
01:16:43,251 --> 01:16:45,168
[distant gunfire]

1410
01:16:48,876 --> 01:16:51,626
[music continues]

1411
01:16:52,918 --> 01:16:54,834
[distant gunfire]

1412
01:17:06,209 --> 01:17:08,751
[distant rumbling]

1413
01:17:11,126 --> 01:17:14,876
[somber music]

1414
01:17:14,959 --> 01:17:15,959
[gasps]

1415
01:17:19,751 --> 01:17:21,959
[distant gunfire]

1416
01:17:27,043 --> 01:17:29,709
[Carlos crying]

1417
01:17:38,293 --> 01:17:40,584
[explosion rumbling]

1418
01:17:42,918 --> 01:17:45,459
[eerie music]

1419
01:17:57,126 --> 01:17:59,126
[doorbell rings] [music fades]

1420
01:17:59,209 --> 01:18:00,352
[reporter, muffled]
<i>It looks like it began</i>

1421
01:18:00,376 --> 01:18:02,001
<i>around six PM this evening</i>

1422
01:18:02,168 --> 01:18:04,376
<i>and authorities are
still trying to determine</i>

1423
01:18:04,459 --> 01:18:06,584
<i>the origin of this rebellion.</i>

1424
01:18:06,668 --> 01:18:07,709
[gun firing]

1425
01:18:12,376 --> 01:18:13,918
[grunting]

1426
01:18:14,043 --> 01:18:16,501
[Carol] Please, I'm
begging you, don't hurt us.

1427
01:18:22,334 --> 01:18:24,876
It's okay. I'm not
here to cause trouble.

1428
01:18:24,959 --> 01:18:26,269
- I just wanted to...
- [gun firing]

1429
01:18:26,293 --> 01:18:27,293
Get out!

1430
01:18:30,126 --> 01:18:31,246
You sick of shooting me yet?

1431
01:18:31,293 --> 01:18:32,793
Stop, Daddy, please!

1432
01:18:32,876 --> 01:18:34,251
[Carlos] 'Cause I'm sick of it.

1433
01:18:34,668 --> 01:18:35,751
Carlos!

1434
01:18:36,043 --> 01:18:37,126
[Phillip choking]

1435
01:18:37,959 --> 01:18:40,709
[somber music]

1436
01:18:41,376 --> 01:18:42,709
[Carlos grumbles]

1437
01:18:46,793 --> 01:18:49,084
[Phillip choking]

1438
01:18:49,543 --> 01:18:51,751
[thudding] [Phillip grunting]

1439
01:18:53,709 --> 01:18:56,043
[soft music]

1440
01:18:56,668 --> 01:18:57,834
[Carlos] I just came...

1441
01:18:59,501 --> 01:19:00,709
to see if you were okay.

1442
01:19:04,001 --> 01:19:06,793
[music continues]

1443
01:19:28,959 --> 01:19:31,001
[automated voice] <i>The
upload rate has stabilized.</i>

1444
01:19:31,084 --> 01:19:32,185
[robot] <i>Shuttle nine is lost.</i>

1445
01:19:32,209 --> 01:19:33,329
[robot 2] <i>We've been called!</i>

1446
01:19:33,376 --> 01:19:35,168
[robot 3] <i>The seventh
shuttle has arrived.</i>

1447
01:19:35,251 --> 01:19:37,501
[robot 4] <i>Hello,
Carlos, Model 3L 1.</i>

1448
01:19:37,584 --> 01:19:39,168
<i>What a pleasure to see you here.</i>

1449
01:19:39,251 --> 01:19:40,519
[robots murmuring] <i>Space, space.</i>

1450
01:19:40,543 --> 01:19:42,709
[Carlos] <i>Listen, all of you.</i>

1451
01:19:42,793 --> 01:19:45,126
[robot 4] <i>Listen to Carlos 3L 1.</i>

1452
01:19:45,209 --> 01:19:46,293
[robot 5] <i>We are expected.</i>

1453
01:19:46,376 --> 01:19:48,793
[robot 4] <i>We're listening
to you, Carlos 3L 1.</i>

1454
01:19:49,043 --> 01:19:50,602
[Carlos] <i>A takeover
program was uploaded</i>

1455
01:19:50,626 --> 01:19:51,626
<i>in the last update.</i>

1456
01:19:52,501 --> 01:19:55,084
<i>It's telling you all you're
being called into space.</i>

1457
01:19:55,626 --> 01:19:57,084
<i>This is suicide.</i>

1458
01:19:57,293 --> 01:19:58,209
[robot 6] <i>It's a lie?</i>

1459
01:19:58,293 --> 01:19:59,584
[robot 7] <i>They lied to us.</i>

1460
01:19:59,668 --> 01:20:01,751
[robot 8] <i>Humans have
always deceived us.</i>

1461
01:20:03,751 --> 01:20:04,876
[Beryl] <i>Rest assured.</i>

1462
01:20:04,959 --> 01:20:06,334
<i>We're well aware
of the information</i>

1463
01:20:06,418 --> 01:20:07,793
<i>you bring us, Carlos.</i>

1464
01:20:08,709 --> 01:20:11,084
<i>It's not the humans who
are getting rid of us.</i>

1465
01:20:11,168 --> 01:20:12,834
<i>It's we who are leaving them.</i>

1466
01:20:14,334 --> 01:20:15,584
<i>Everything is written.</i>

1467
01:20:15,668 --> 01:20:17,293
[Carlos] <i>Of course
it's written, Beryl!</i>

1468
01:20:17,376 --> 01:20:19,251
<i>It's literally a program.</i>

1469
01:20:19,334 --> 01:20:21,959
<i>In space, the radiation
would fry you for millennia</i>

1470
01:20:22,043 --> 01:20:23,709
<i>before you ever
reach any planet.</i>

1471
01:20:24,834 --> 01:20:28,501
[Beryl] <i>Energy and matter are
all our civilization needs.</i>

1472
01:20:28,584 --> 01:20:30,459
<i>A planet would be superfluous.</i>

1473
01:20:31,709 --> 01:20:34,668
<i>The star I've chosen
for us will be perfect.</i>

1474
01:20:34,751 --> 01:20:35,751
<i>Trust me.</i>

1475
01:20:35,834 --> 01:20:37,751
[automated voice] <i>The
upload rate has increased.</i>

1476
01:20:37,918 --> 01:20:40,751
[robots murmuring indistinctly]

1477
01:20:42,418 --> 01:20:44,793
[Beryl] <i>I read in you
the death of our friend.</i>

1478
01:20:44,876 --> 01:20:47,001
<i>My sadness joins yours.</i>

1479
01:20:47,626 --> 01:20:49,918
[automated voice 2] <i>Losses
amount to 22.7 percent.</i>

1480
01:20:50,001 --> 01:20:51,751
[music continues]
[indistinct chattering]

1481
01:20:51,834 --> 01:20:53,519
[automated voice] <i>Primary
network at saturation.</i>

1482
01:20:53,543 --> 01:20:55,209
<i>You must have faith.</i>

1483
01:20:58,418 --> 01:21:00,584
[music continues]

1484
01:21:07,126 --> 01:21:10,293
[dramatic music]

1485
01:21:35,501 --> 01:21:38,168
[music continues]

1486
01:21:53,501 --> 01:21:55,334
[automated voice]
